28821  10-DRIVE OFF Timeout in drives activation 

       Cause:
         Drives do not reply to the activation request. 

       Remedy:
         Check the led state on the safety board.  Report the conditions
         which caused the problem to COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


28822  10-DRIVE OFF Timeout <command_type> (phase:<number>") 

       Cause:
         The DRIVE-ON procedure has been aborted due to a timeout on the
         command duration. 

       Remedy:
         Re-issue the DRIVE-ON command again. 


28823  10-DRIVE OFF Timeout <command_type> (phase:<number>") 

       Cause:
         The timeout associated to the DRIVE-OFF execution exphired. 


28824  0-INFO 


28825  0-INFO 


28826  0-INFO 


28827  0-INFO 


28828  11-DRIVE OFF ENABLE <channel> anomaly in the SDM board 

       Cause:
         Enable 1 ($SDI[57]) and/or enable 2 ($SDI[56]) of the safety board
         are not in the correct state during the DRIVE ON procedure. 

       Remedy:
         Check the state of the safety board inputs ($SDI[57] and $SDI[56])
         and the related connections.

28830  0-INFO 


28831  0-INFO 


28832  11-DRIVE OFF Bad drives activation 

       Cause:
         The drives replied with a nack to the activation request. The
         system did not enter the DRIVE-ON state. 

       Remedy:
         Check the drives modules. 


28833  11-DRIVE OFF Bad drives enabling(sts:<state>, Arm:0x<arm_mask>) 

       Cause:
         The drives replied with a nack to the activation request. The
         system did not enter the DRIVE-ON state. 

       Remedy:
         Check the drives modules. 


28834  2-WARNING Anomaly on jog keys 

       Cause:
         The disabling, during state transitions, of jog keys (1+, 1-,
         2+,...) on the teach pendant did not properly work. 

       Remedy:
         Check that jog keys properly work. 


28835  2-WARNING Jog keys not enabled 

       Cause:
         Jog keys (1+, 1-, 2+,...) on the teach pendant, used for manual
         motion, have not been properly enabled. 

       Remedy:
         Check that jog keys properly work. 


28836  0-INFO 


28837  0-INFO 


28838  11-DRIVE OFF Drives are not in the active state 

       Cause:
         Drives are not ready for DRIVE-ON. 

       Remedy:
         Check the status of drives. 


28839  11-DRIVE OFF Drives are not in the disabled state
       (Arm:0x<arm_mask>) 

       Cause:
         Drives did not disabled. 

       Remedy:
         Check the status of drives. 


28840  2-WARNING Minimal configuration, not <file_name> 

       Cause:
         The system started in minimal configuration. The .C5G file is not
         present or is wrong, In this conditions the DRIVE-ON and/or HOLD
         command is not allowed. 

       Remedy:
         Verify if the .C5G file is present and, if not, load the correct
         one and restart the system. 


28841  11-DRIVE OFF Anomaly (<command>) of safety relay (cnl <channel>) on
       system board 

       Cause:
         The system board safety relay did not change the state upon a close
         or open command. The relay could be broken. 

       Remedy:
         Check the status of the system CAN node. Check also the state of
         the safety board and the system board relay. 


28842  2-WARNING Holdable program not active 

       Cause:
         A START command has been issued but no holdable program has
         previously been activated. 

       Remedy:
         Activate the program before issuing the START. 


28843  2-WARNING DRIVE ON only allowed from TP key 

       Cause:
         The system received a DRIVE ON request in the AUTO-L state upon the
         enabling device pressure. In AUTO-L this command is only allowed
         upon teach pendant key pressure. 

       Remedy:
         Use the DRIVE ON key and release the enabling device. 


28844  2-WARNING Data saving after power down 

       Cause:
         The controller detected a power down. The system has started a data
         saving operation and the restore of them. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message. 


28845  0-INFO 


28846  11-DRIVE OFF Anomaly of enabling device (cnl <channel>) 

       Cause:
         Input 42 (channel 2 , $SDI[42]) or 45 (channel 1,  $SDI[45]) of the
         safety board did not properly change the state. The enabling device
         previously hasn't been released completely before DRIVE-ON command
         or it could be damaged. 

       Remedy:
         Re-issue DRIVE-ON by pressing the enabling device after it has been
         released completely. If the problem persists, check and eventually
         replace the enabling device and inputs 45 ($SDI[45]) and 46
         ($SDI[46]) on safety board. 


28847  2-WARNING AUTO-T, maximum allowed speed: 100 % 

       Cause:
         The system is ready to START the active holdable program, which
         movement could be executed also at 100% of speed. The user must be
         careful to move the robot inside the working area. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message. 


28848  0-INFO 


28849  2-WARNING The enabling device is available on TP only 

       Cause:
         The selector of the enabling device on the controller cabinet is
         set to enable the enabling device on the TP. Pressing the enabling
         device on the SLJ has no effect. 

       Remedy:
         Set the selector of the enabling device on the controller cabinet
         according to the device that you are going to use. 


28850  2-WARNING The enabling device is available on SLJ only 

       Cause:
         The selector of the enabling device on the controller cabinet is
         set to enable the enabling device on the SLJ. Pressing the enabling
         device on the TP has no effect. 

       Remedy:
         Set the selector of the enabling device on the controller cabinet
         according to the device that you are going to use. 


28851  2-WARNING Warning: low memory on board 

       Cause:
         The system board has few memory left. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message. 


28852  2-WARNING Warning : little memory 

       Cause:
         The board has few memory left. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message. 


28853  13-FATAL Memory error: <task_id>n <part_id> <block_id> 

       Cause:
         Internal system error. 

       Remedy:
         Refer to COMAU  (service.robotics@comau.com) the situation that
         caused the problem and the related parameters. 


28854  13-FATAL Memory error:  <task_id>n <part_id> <block_id> 

       Cause:
         Internal system error. 

       Remedy:
         Refer to COMAU  (service.robotics@comau.com) the situation that
         caused the problem and the related parameters. 


28855  0-INFO 


28856  2-WARNING Automatic DRIVE-ON feature enabled 

       Cause:
         The automatic drive-on feature is enabled. This means that, when
         the system is in the "LOCAL" state, the READY state is the primary
         one if no conditions that could stop a DRIVE ON exist. In this way,
         the user should not press the DRIVE-ON key on the TP. 

       Remedy:
         This feature can be disabled by pressing the DRIVE-OFF key when the
         READY state is active. 


28857  2-WARNING Feature not available in the current state of the system 

       Cause:
         The requested feature cannot be enabled due to the state of the
         system that is in the minimal configuration or in fatal error. 

       Remedy:
         Restart the system in order to re-enable the feature. 


28858  2-WARNING Automatic-Local modality activated 

       Cause:
         The automatic-local modality, which allows to the user to control
         the system, from the teach pendant, has been selected. Under these
         conditions, although the state selector is switched to remote
         (automatic-mode), the system ignores any command that is not coming
         from the teach pendant. This operation causes, for safety reasons,
         a machine DRIVE-OFF. 

       Remedy:
         For restoring the production automatic modality (remote), change
         the value of the proper system variable. 


28859  2-WARNING Automatic-Local modality deactivated 

       Cause:
         The automatic-local modality, which allows to the user to control
         the system, from the teach pendant, has been deactivated. The
         system is running in the automatic production modality (remote),
         with the selector positioned to remote. This operation causes, for
         safety reasons, a machine DRIVE-OFF. 

       Remedy:
         For changing modality, properly set the related system variable. 


28860  0-INFO <SDM> inconsistent inputs 


28861  2-WARNING Please acknowledge latched alarms before DRIVE ON 

       Cause:
         The system requires that all pending latched allarms are
         acknowledged before entering the DRIVE-ON state. This restriction
         is not present when the state of system is PROG. 

       Remedy:
         For switching the drives on, when the system is in the automatic
         mode, the user must acknowledge the active latched alarms first. 


28862  2-WARNING Please acknowledge latched alarms for entering automatic
       mode 

       Cause:
         The system requires that all pending latched allarms are
         acknowledged before entering the automatic mode. Until then the
         START command is not allowed although the state selector is on the
         automatic position. 

       Remedy:
         For switching in automatic mode, the user must acknowledge the
         active latched alarms first. 


28863  2-WARNING %s: Safety speed 

       Cause:
         This message indicates that the SAFETY SPEED request is active from
         remote. In this situation it is not possible to increase the speed
         more than 250 mm/sec, because the system is enabled to satisfy the
         requests coming from remote. 

       Remedy:
         In order to disable this feature, please issue, in a state
         different than REMOTE, the SetInputRemoteDisable command. In this
         way the remote interface is temporarely disabled until the next
         system state change or until the next SetInputRemoteEnable command. 


28864  2-WARNING START not allowed during HOLD 

       Cause:
         The system received a START request during the HOLD procedure. 

       Remedy:
         Wait the robot stops and re-issue the START command. 


28865  2-WARNING AUX_DRIVES: opzion not configured 

       Cause:
         The AUX_DRIVES built-in has been executed on a system that does not
         include this option. 

       Remedy:
         The AUX_DRIVES routine is only allowed on robot configurations
         which foreseen auxiliary axes. Please verify if the controller is
         correctly configured and eventually ask for a new configuration
         file. 


28866  2-WARNING AUX_DRIVES function in progress 

       Cause:
         A command which mismatches with the AUX_DRIVES function has been
         issued meanwhile the AUX_DRIVES is in progress. Forbidden commands
         are: another AUX_DRIVES, an AUX_SET or a DRIVE ON. 

       Remedy:
         Please wait the completion of the first operation before issuing
         the command. It could be needed to synchronize some processes. 


28867  2-WARNING AUX_DRIVES disallowed during other commands 

       Cause:
         AUX_DRIVES has been issued meanwhile a command related to motors
         was is progress. AUX_DRIVES is disallowed meanwhile one of the
         following operations are in progress: DRIVE ON, DRIVE OFF, "energy
         saving" enabling /disabling and power failure recovery. 

       Remedy:
         Try executing again the  AUX_DRIVES function when noone of the
         above command is in progress. Try sunchronizing the program which
         issues AUX_DRIVES  with the other processes. 


28868  10-DRIVE OFF AUX_DRIVES: failure in <procedure name> procedure
       (phase:<number> err:<error_num>) 

       Cause:
         The system board did not complete the AUX_DRIVES routine execution. 

       Remedy:
         Please try reproducing the sequence of operations which caused the
         problem and contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


28869  0-INFO 


28870  4-PAUSE Exchangeable axis not connected 

       Cause:
         AUX_SET(ON) detected that the hardware connection (motor or
         position transducer) to the axis has not been done. This is a
         necessary condition for the execution. 

       Remedy:
         Please check the axis connection and repeat the procedure. 


28871  1-INFO Recovering from power failure 

       Cause:
         The system is restarting after a power failure. 

       Remedy:
         Please wait the completione of the recovery provedure. 


28872  1-INFO  ## SYSTEM IN MINIMAL CONFIGURATION ## 

       Cause:
         The system entered the minimal configuration. 

       Remedy:
         Please restore a normal situation by loading the correct
         configuration file. 


28873  1-INFO TP disconnected in PROG/AUTO-T 

       Cause:
         The Teach Pendant has been disconnected when the state of the
         system was PROG or AUTO-T. Input n. 24 of the safety board is low. 

       Remedy:
         Reconnect the Teach Pendant to the safety board. 


28874  1-INFO TP disconnected in DRIVE-OFF 

       Cause:
         The Teach Pendant has been disconnected when the motors were
         switched off. Input n. 24 of the safety board is low. 

       Remedy:
         Reconnect the Teach Pendant to the safety board. 


28875  1-INFO TP disconnected in HOLD 

       Cause:
         The Teach Pendant has been disconnected when the motors was in the
         HOLD state. Input n. 24 of the safety board is low. 

       Remedy:
         Reconnect the Teach Pendant to the safety board. 


28876  1-INFO TP disconnected in DRIVE-OFF+HOLD 

       Cause:
         The Teach Pendant has been disconnected when the system was in the
         HOLD state and when the motors were switched off. Input n. 24 of
         the safety board is low. 

       Remedy:
         Reconnect the Teach Pendant to the safety board. 


28877  1-INFO TP safety test:remove TP from cabinet 

       Cause:
         The system needs to register a transition of the enabling device of
         the teach pendant; it could be enough to remove the TP out of its
         location on the cabinet. This is a safety test which is active only
         upon the first transition of the system in PROG or AUTO-T state. 

       Remedy:
         Press and release the enabling device, or remove the TP from the
         cabinet. 


28878  1-INFO DRIVE-OFF from enabling device 

       Cause:
         The system switched the motors off due to the pressing/releasing of
         the enabling device. 

       Remedy:
         Please also check that the enabling device is correctly working. 


28879  1-INFO Press the enabling device for AUTO-T 

       Cause:
         The system warns the user that, in AUTO-T, the motors can be
         switched on pressing the enabling device. 


28880  1-INFO Put the TP on cabinet for AUTO 

       Cause:
         In order to enter the Automatic state, the system needs to detect a
         transition of the device which informs about the TP location. This
         device is positioned in the back side of the TP itself. 

       Remedy:
         Please put the TP in the holder on the controller cabinet. 


28881  1-INFO Alarms exclusion 

       Cause:
         The system detected the pressure, in PROG, of the EXCL teach
         pendant key. This message informs the user that hardware
         stroke-ends are excluded in a 60 sec. time. Under these conditions,
         it is possible to move the robot using JOG/JPAD keys. 

       Remedy:
         After 60 seconds, this message will automatically be removed, and
         stroke ends will be restored. 


28882  1-INFO Active 'latched' alarms to confirm 

       Cause:
         Some alarms triggered and need to be confirmed by the user. These
         category of alarms are called latched alarms. 

       Remedy:
         Please confirm the latched alarms. 


28883  1-INFO DRIVE-OFF from fieldbus 

       Cause:
         The system received a DRIVE OFF command from remote. Under these
         conditions, motors cannot be switched on. 

       Remedy:
         Please check that remote commands have been activated with the
         proper sequence. In case it is needed, in a system state different
         from REMOTE, to switch in DRIVE ON, issue the SetInputRemoteDisable
         command. In this way the remote interface is temporarely disabled
         until the next system state change or until the next
         SetInputRemoteEnable command. 


28884  1-INFO HOLD from fieldbus 

       Cause:
         The system received a HOLD command from remote. 

       Remedy:
         Please check that remote commands have been activated with the
         proper sequence. In case it is needed, in a system state different
         from REMOTE, to switch in DRIVE ON, issue the SetInputRemoteDisable
         command. In this way the remote interface is temporarely disabled
         until the next system state change or until the next
         SetInputRemoteEnable command. 


28885  1-INFO DRIVE-OFF+HOLD from fieldbus 

       Cause:
         The system received a DRIVE OFF + HOLD command from remote. Under
         these conditions, motors cannot be switched on. 

       Remedy:
         Please check that remote commands have been activated with the
         proper sequence. In case it is needed, in a system state different
         from REMOTE, to switch in DRIVE ON, issue the SetInputRemoteDisable
         command. In this way the remote interface is temporarely disabled
         until the next system state change or until the next
         SetInputRemoteEnable command. 


28886  1-INFO Safety speed from fieldbus 

       Cause:
         The system received, from a fieldbus source, the command of moving
         at the safety speed. Under these conditions, it is not possible to
         move the robot at a faster speed than the safety one. 

       Remedy:
         In order to move faster, it is needed to stop the source of the
         command. 


28887  1-INFO DRIVE-OFF from remote 

       Cause:
         The system received a DRIVE OFF command from remote. Under these
         conditions, motors cannot be switched on. 

       Remedy:
         Please check that remote commands have been activated with the
         proper sequence. In case it is needed, in a system state different
         from REMOTE, to switch in DRIVE ON, issue the SetInputRemoteDisable
         command. In this way the remote interface is temporarely disabled
         until the next system state change or until the next
         SetInputRemoteEnable command. 


28888  1-INFO HOLD from remote 

       Cause:
         The system received a HOLD command from remote. 

       Remedy:
         Please check that remote commands have been activated with the
         proper sequence. In case it is needed, in a system state different
         from REMOTE, to switch in DRIVE ON, issue the SetInputRemoteDisable
         command. In this way the remote interface is temporarely disabled
         until the next system state change or until the next
         SetInputRemoteEnable command. 


28889  1-INFO DRIVE-OFF+HOLD from remote 

       Cause:
         The system received a DRIVE OFF + HOLD command from remote. Under
         these conditions, motors cannot be switched on. 

       Remedy:
         Please check that remote commands have been activated with the
         proper sequence. In case it is needed, in a system state different
         from REMOTE, to switch in DRIVE ON, issue the SetInputRemoteDisable
         command. In this way the remote interface is temporarely disabled
         until the next system state change or until the next
         SetInputRemoteEnable command. 


28890  1-INFO Release START/BACK/jog keys on TP 

       Cause:
         START/BACK/jog keys of the teach pendant need to be released in
         order to manually move the robot. 

       Remedy:
         In order to manually move the robot, release one of the indicated
         keys first. 


28891  1-INFO Safety on gates excluded 

       Cause:
         The system advises the user that there is an holdable program
         running in AUTO-T and the motion is commanded by the steady
         pressure of the START key on the TP. 

       Remedy:
         This message warns the user about the exclusion, in AUTO-T, of the
         safety gates test. 


28892  4-PAUSE Rotating table: arm <arm_num> not configured 

       Cause:
         The rotating table cannot be started because the system is not
         configured for handling it. 

       Remedy:
         The switching on of rotating tables is only allowed on specific
         robot configurations which foresee arms identifiable with tables.
         Check that the configuration is correct and, if necessary, ask for
         a new configuration file. 


28893  2-WARNING Rotating table: procedure <procedure_name> in progress
       (arm<arm_num>) 

       Cause:
         The requested command is not allowed during a start/stop procedure
         of a rotating table. Cannot execute at the same time AUX_DRIVES or
         AUX_SET on the same arm. 

       Remedy:
         Please wait for the completion of the previous command and reissue
         the one which failed. Synchronize processes which require the
         execution of those commands. 


28894  2-WARNING Rotating table: procedure not allowed during other
       commands 

       Cause:
         The starting procedure of the rotating table has been issued while
         another command is handling the motors. It is not allowed
         contemporaneously to: DRIVE ON, DRIVE OFF, enabling or disabling of
         the "energy saving" state, AUX_DRIVES and AUX_SET built-in routines
         on the same arm, power failure recovery and system  in minimal
         configuration. 

       Remedy:
         Try executing again the procedure when none of the above commands
         is in progress. Try synchronizing the program which is executing
         the AUX_DRIVES built-in with processed which require other
         commands. 


28895  0-INFO 


28896  0-INFO 


28897  0-INFO 


28898  2-WARNING Rotating table: command refused due to open safety inputs
       ($GI[<port_index>]) on arm<arm_num> 

       Cause:
         The system could not start the Motor ON procedure for the rotating
         table, due to the open safety inputs request through the indicated
         port. The system disallows the starting of the table until all
         consents are given. 

       Remedy:
         Remove the MOTOR OFF condition for moving the table. 


28899  2-WARNING Rotating table: command refused due to Motor Off request
       ($GI[<port_index>]) on arm<arm_num> 

       Cause:
         The system could not start the Motor ON procedure for the rotating
         table, due to a MOTOR OFF request, on the indicated port. The
         system disallows the starting of the table until all consents are
         given. 

       Remedy:
         Remove the OFF condition for moving the table. 


28900  10-DRIVE OFF Signals for rotating table change too frequently 

       Cause:
         The system software reads, at least every 10 milliseconds, the
         signals incoming from the rotating tables. If these signals change
         too frequently, the system cannot execute the related commands. 

       Remedy:
         Check the connections to the rotating tables and to the linked
         devices or to the sources of signals. 


28901  2-WARNING Rotating table: start (arm<arm_num>) refused because the
       system is not Running 

       Cause:
         The system board could not start the indicated rotating table,
         because the system is not in the running state. This means that no
         arm of the controller is moving. 

       Remedy:
         Press the START button from TP. 


28902  2-WARNING Arm<arm_num> already started 

       Cause:
         The system received the START command for an arm which is already
         moving. 


28903  2-WARNING Entering T1P  state 

       Cause:
         The T1P  state is selected by the position of T2 in the state
         selector. 

       Remedy:
         Unlatch this alarm for operating in this state of the system.
         Please be careful to press the START when the DRIVES are ON because
         the robot will move at the current speed, even if the maximum one.
         Safety on gates is automatically excluded. 


28904  10-DRIVE OFF Timeout drives disabling (Arm:0x<arm_mask>) 

       Cause:
         The system did not receive replies to the request of drives
         disabling. 

       Remedy:
         Re-issue the command and, if the problem persists, check the drives
         present in the system. 


28905  10-DRIVE OFF Timeout drives enabling (Arm:0x<arm_mask>) 

       Cause:
         The system did not receive replies to the request of enabling and,
         as a consequence, it did not enter the ON state. 

       Remedy:
         Re-issue the command and, if the problem persists, check the drives
         present in the system. 


28906  10-DRIVE OFF Error <error> during the command <type_of_command>
       (phase:<phase_number>, Arm:0x<arm_mask>) 

       Cause:
         An error has been generated during the ON procedure. The specified
         drives are the source of the message itself. 

       Remedy:
         Re-issue the command or reset the system. If the problem persists,
         contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com), reporting the
         parameters associated to the error. 


28907  10-DRIVE OFF Timeout reading the Arm memory (Arm:0x<arm_mask>) 

       Cause:
         The system did not receive any answer to the memory read requests.
         The system did not enter the ON state. 

       Remedy:
         Re-issue the command and, if the problem persists, check the drives
         modules present in the system. 


28908  10-DRIVE OFF Error:<packet_error> reading the Arm memory
       (Arm:0x<arm_mask>) 

       Cause:
         The system received a negative answer to the request of reading the
         memory. The system did not enter the ON state. 

       Remedy:
         Re-issue the command and, if the problem persists, check the drives
         present in the system. 


28909  11-DRIVE OFF Drives disabling failed (sts:<state>,
       Arm:0x<arm_mask>) 

       Cause:
         The drives did not reply to the disabling request. 

       Remedy:
         Re-issue the command and, if the problem persists, check the drives
         present in the system. 


28910  2-WARNING T1P , speed limited to safety speed 

       Cause:
         The test modality  foresees the limitation in the speed to the
         programming state. The operator must pay attention in moving the
         robot inside the working area. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message. 


28911  11-DRIVE OFF CPU busy at <percentage> percent of <task>n task 

       Cause:
         This is an internal system error. 

       Remedy:
         Please refer to COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com) the sequence of
         operation which caused this error and the parameters associate to
         this message. 


28912  13-FATAL System board CPU busy at <percentage> percent of  <task>n
       task 

       Cause:
         This is an internal system error. 

       Remedy:
         Please refer to COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com) the sequence of
         operation which caused this error and the parameters associate to
         this message. 


28913  4-PAUSE Arm not accessible 

       Cause:
         A request has been sent to the axis of an arm which has not been
         selected before. It is always needed to select first the arm on
         which operating, both in case it is the current arm or the
         synchronized one. 

       Remedy:
         Please select the arm to be referred as current or synchronized
         arm. 


28914  0-INFO 


28915  2-WARNING Pairing with WiTP in progress 

       Cause:
         The procedure for the connection between the wireless teach-pendant
         and the controller is in progress. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. 


28916  2-WARNING Unpairing with WiTP in progress 

       Cause:
         The procedure for the disconnection of the wireless teach-pendant
         and the controller is in progress. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. 


28917  2-WARNING Forced unpairing of the WiTP in progress 

       Cause:
         The emergency procedure for the forced disconnection of the
         wireless teach-pendant from the controller is running. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. 


28918  2-WARNING Forced unpairing button has been pressed 

       Cause:
         The electronic of the safety board requires the user to perform the
         emergency procedure for the forced unpairing with the WiTP, in
         order to restore its correct functioning. 

       Remedy:
         Execute the emergency procedure for unpairing the WiTP. 


28919  2-WARNING WiTP pairing failed 

       Cause:
         The pairing  procedure between WiTP and the controller failed. The
         system automatically restores the WiTP upaired state, which means
         that no wireless teach-pendant is connected. 

       Remedy:
         In order to use the wireless teach-pendant, repeat the operation.
         In case of failure, please check the state of the ESM and of WiTP.
         At the end, please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


28920  2-WARNING No paired WiTP 

       Cause:
         No wireless teach-pendant is paired to the controller. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. Perform a pairing operation. 


28921  10-DRIVE OFF Signals from the ESM board change too frequently 

       Cause:
         The system software reads the signals coming from the electronic
         safety board at least once every 10 milliseconds. If these signals
         change too frequently, the system is disallowed to perform external
         commands. 

       Remedy:
         Please check the board connection to remote signals or to the
         sources of these signals (CAN, PLC,..). 


28922  1-INFO AccessPoint device not configured 

       Cause:
         The AP device of the controller is not configured. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. Under these conditions, the
         controller cannot establish wireless connections. 


28923  4-PAUSE Access Point device configuration failed 

       Cause:
         The configuration of the robot controller access point (AP) for the
         wireless connection failed. Under these conditions, no wireless
         device can reach the robot controller. The pairing procedure is
         automatically inhibited. 

       Remedy:
         Please check that the access point is switched on or reset the
         hardware. 


28924  2-WARNING New ESM board 

       Cause:
         The system detected a new electronic safety  board (ESM). 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message. 


28925  2-WARNING Please wait for the configuration of the AccessPoint
       device 

       Cause:
         The Access Point device of the controller has not been configured
         yet. 

       Remedy:
         Before trying unpairing the WiTP to the robot controller, please
         wait for the completion of the configuration of the Access Point
         device. This operation, if performed for the first time, could also
         require fifty seconds about. 


28926  4-PAUSE ESM board not recognized 

       Cause:
         The system detected a new safety electronic board (ESM) which has
         not recognized as a valid one. 

       Remedy:
         Check the state of the ESM board, of the CAN module and related
         connections. 


28927  1-INFO System not ready for pairing to WiTP 

       Cause:
         The system is not ready yet for accomplishing a pairing request.
         Under these conditions, the controller is not able to establish a
         connection with WiTP. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. It is necessary to wait that the
         system has completed the startup. 


28928  1-INFO Access Point device restart is in progress 

       Cause:
         The reconfiguration of the Access Point device of the controller is
         in progress. 

       Remedy:
         Please wait for the completion of the Access Point restore
         procedure. The pairing of the WiTP  to the robot controller will
         only be possible after the restore of the Access Point. 


28929  2-WARNING Access Point device restart has completed 

       Cause:
         The Access Point device of the controller has been reconfigured. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message. 


28930  2-WARNING Access Point device is active 

       Cause:
         The AP (Access Point) device of the controller is active. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational messge. Under these conditions, the
         controller can establish a wireless connection with WiTP. 


28931  11-DRIVE OFF Anomaly in electronic safety boards (sts:<bit-mask>) 

       Cause:
         The electronic safety board (ESM) is in error. 

       Remedy:
         Under these conditions, it is not possible to switch drives on.
         Please report the error parameters to COMAU
         (service.robotics@comau.com). It could be needed  to eventually
         replace the board. 


28932  2-WARNING Low reactivity on disconnections of TP keys
       0x<read_timeout>, <upd_timeout> 

       Cause:
         The system is working with a timeout for the TP disconnection
         greater that 500 ms. Under these conditions, please be careful when
         moving the robot, in particular at high speed. This is an
         informational message but requires an acknowledge from the user, in
         order to allow the motors to be switched on. 

       Remedy:
         Please confirm the alarm if it is needed to switch motors on. 


28933  0-INFO 


28934  2-WARNING Error <error> during unpairing 

       Cause:
         The system detected an error while polling the WiTP during the
         unpairing procedure. 

       Remedy:
         If the WiTP need to be paired, repeat the pairing procedure and in
         case of multiple anomalies, please report this error to COMAU
         (service.robotics@comau.com). 


28935  1-INFO Access Point device configuration failed 

       Cause:
         The Access Point (AP) configuration for the wireless connection to
         the robot controller failed. Under these conditions, no wireless
         device can reach the robot controller. The pairing procedure is
         automatically inhibited. 

       Remedy:
         Please check that the access point device is switched on and
         properly connected. Please reset the hardware restarting the
         system. This is an informational message. 


28936  11-DRIVE OFF Emergency stop for disconnected WiTP 

       Cause:
         Input 41($SDI[41]) and 42 ($SDI[42]) on safety boards are low,
         indicating that the stop contactors of the emergency stop button
         are open due to the disconnection of the teach pendant. The WiTP is
         still paired to the robot controller but does not communicate.
         Under these conditions, it is not possible to switch motors on
         until the connection is not restored or the teach pendant is not
         unpaired. 

       Remedy:
         Please check that the WiTP is switched on in order to restore the
         Wi-Fi communication, checking the absence of obstacoles. In case
         the communication is not restored, please restart the robot
         controller or follow the emergency uncoupling procedure and then
         issue the controller restart. 


28937  4-PAUSE Paired TP: low battery level 

       Cause:
         The system detected a very low battery level.  It is necessary to
         charge the battery, otherwise the TP will uncouple causing the lost
         of connection with the robot controller. Under these conditions, in
         order to make operative again the controller, it will be needed to
         execute the emergency unpairing procedure. 

       Remedy:
         Charge the TP, putting it on the Docking-Station, or uncouple it in
         order to avoid the lost of connection and the machine stop. 


28938  2-WARNING TP battery level is low 

       Cause:
         The battery level of the TP is low. Under these conditions, if the
         TP battery completely discharges, it uncouples with the C3G
         controller. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. Recharge the TP. 


28939  0-INFO 


28940  10-DRIVE OFF Cannot DRIVE ON due to error 

       Cause:
         Due to an error, the DRIVE ON cannot be accomplished. 

       Remedy:
         The hardware problem has to be identified and solved. If an
         hardware component is broken, please replace it AFTER having
         switched the controller off. It is not required a complete system
         restart. 


28941  11-DRIVE OFF Stop button 

       Cause:
         Inputs 49 ($SDI[49]) and 50 ($SDI[50]) on the safety board are low.
         This means that contacts of the stop button in the wireless teach
         pendant have been opened. 

       Remedy:
         Close the contacts of the stop button, restoring the button itself. 


28942  2-WARNING Check that MGD is unmounted from the robot 

       Cause:
         The MGD could be mounted on the robot: before entering
         Local/Remote/T2 states, you have to confirm that the MGD has been
         unmounted. 

       Remedy:
         Unlatch this alarm ONLY after having unmounted the MGD from the
         robot in order to avoid the projection of the device while the
         robot is operating in automatic modes. 


28943  11-DRIVE OFF SDM diagnostic - $SDI[<port_index>] (sts : 0x<status>) 

       Cause:
         The SDM board detected an error during self-diagnosis. The status
         (sts) information encodes the $SDI[89..96] bits. Least significant
         bit corresponds to $SDI[89], while the most significant bit
         corresponds to $SDI[96]. 

       Remedy:
         Switch OFF and ON the controller, in order to repeat SDM board
         self-diagnosis. If $SDI[89] bit is zero, please check if the error
         disappears ($SDI[89] bit returns to 1) disconnecting cables on
         X108/SDM, X109/SDM connectors. If error is cleared disconnecting
         cable at X108, the issue is caused by main enable circuit. If error
         is cleared disconnecting cable at X109, the issue is caused by the
         auxiliary enable circuit. If one of $SDI[91] or $SDI[92] bits is
         zero, please check if the error disappears disconnecting the flat
         cable attached to X10/SDM. If error clears, the issue may be caused
         by the flat cable at X10 or by ERM1 board. In case all above
         troubleshooting fail, replace SDM board. 


28944  10-DRIVE OFF SDM configuration  TP Wired/Wireless not OK - $SDI[82] 

       Cause:
         The configuration of the terminal is inconsistent. 

       Remedy:
         Please check the cables on X302 and X110 connectors. Ignore this
         indication if contemporarely present with the SDM diagnostic error
         - $SDI[10]. 


28945  10-DRIVE OFF SDM mismatching stop time selectors - $SDI[83] 

       Cause:
         The selected value with the SW1 and Sw2 rotary switches is not the
         same. 

       Remedy:
         Please input the same value. 


28946  8-HOLD SDM anomaly in the power supply state V24SAFE - $SDI[84] 

       Cause:
         Voltage on the 24V SAFE module has been detected when it is not
         provided anymore by the SDM. 

       Remedy:
         If the problem only occurs upon the DRIVE OFF command, please check
         that the loads linked to the 24V SAFE supply do not exceed in
         parallel capacity. In case, isolate the loads with a diode in
         series. If the problem occurs upon DRIVE ON command, please check
         that no tensions are present on the connections due to couplings of
         motor cables powered by the command. 


28947  10-DRIVE OFF SDM Enable 1 output in short circuit - $SDI[85] 

       Cause:
         The self-diagnosis of the Enable 1 output detected a failure or an
         error in the connection which disallows the switching off of the
         controller (voltage lower than 2,5V in the off state). 

       Remedy:
         Please check the cables of the auxiliary axes eventually present,
         disconnect X108 and X109 connectors and issue a switching off/on of
         the system in order to verify if the voltage comes from the extern
         of the SDM module or if there is a damage in the output circuits of
         the module. 


28948  11-DRIVE OFF The system state manager is receiving too many events 

       Cause:
         It is possible that some PDL2 builtins/statements requiring an
         update of the state of the system like ERR_POST, CANCEL ALARM etc
         are executed very quickly. 

       Remedy:
         If the problem is identified into a PDL2 program, it is necessary
         to verify the logic of the program and optimize the requests to the
         system. 


28949  10-DRIVE OFF SDM error on input state selector - $SDI[97] 

       Cause:
         The self-diagnosis of the inputs related to the state selector
         detected a connection error. 

       Remedy:
         Please replace the TP and verify if the problem disappears. 


28950  10-DRIVE OFF SDM error on input for enabling device TP - $SDI[98] 

       Cause:
         The self-diagnosis of the two input channels of the enabling device
         detected an error. The connection of the two channels with the
         related two pulsed signals is not correct. 

       Remedy:
         Please check the cable connected to the X110 of the SDM and the
         programming unit. In case inversions or short circuits in the
         connections are not found, please replace the SDM board. 


28951  10-DRIVE OFF SDM error on input connector X30 - $SDI[99] 

       Cause:
         The self-diagnosis of the Ext. E.Stop, Auto-Stop, Gen. Stop inputs
         detected an error. 

       Remedy:
         Disconnect the X30 connector or the X122 one (if the Profinet Safe
         option is present). Switch the controller off and on and check if
         the error persists. If the error disappears, please check the
         connections to the X30 and X122 connectors and the associated
         devices. If the error appears also without the links, please
         replace the SDM module. 


28952  10-DRIVE OFF SDM error on input of monitor stop button - $SDI[100] 

       Cause:
         The input is not properly connected to the pulsed signal of the
         self-diagnosis input. 

       Remedy:
         Check the cabling of the programming unit and/or replace the TP in
         order to verify the malfunction. 


28953  2-WARNING SDM Power Control communication retry - $SDI[106] 

       Cause:
         A noise has been detected in the SDM internal communication between
         the microcontroller which monitors the power supplies and the
         microcontroller which communicates with the APC820. The
         communication is repeated and the information about the state of
         the power supply are transferred in any case. 

       Remedy:
         The noises can be mitigated putting proper ferrites on the power
         cord of the brake release unit, on the optional kit for the
         additional brake, on the Enable and/or 24V power supply cables of
         the SDM. 


28954  10-DRIVE OFF SDM absence of power V24 on X100 - $SDI[107] 

       Cause:
         The 24V power on the X100 connector, coming from the AMS32 module,
         is missing. 

       Remedy:
         The error usually occurs during the switching off/on phases caused
         by a black-out. In other cases, please check the presence of the
         24V I/O and 24V INT power: if absents, please check the presence of
         the power cable of the X100 connector. 


28955  8-HOLD SDM absence of power V24 after JP200 - $SDI[108] 

       Cause:
         The 24V power in output from the JP200 connector is missing. This
         connector selects the supply internally from the controller (X100)
         or from the extern (X30). 

       Remedy:
         Please check if the JP200 selects the external supply and if this
         is present. 


28956  8-HOLD SDM absence of power V24SAFE in DriveOn - $SDI[109] 

       Cause:
         The V24SAFE power in the DRIVE ON state is missing. This supply is
         inserted upon DRIVE ON and disconnected upon DRIVE OFF. 

       Remedy:
         The error usually occurs during the switching off/on phases due to
         a black-out. Try to issue DRIVE ON and check the presence of the
         voltage on the X106 connector. Please check if  short-circuits are
         present by disconnecting the X12x connectors. 


28957  8-HOLD SDM absence of power V24 I/O - $SDI[111] 

       Cause:
         The 24V I/O supply dedicated to the multibus cable and to the
         applications is missing. 

       Remedy:
         Please check that an overload or a short circuit is not present. If
         it comes out with the overload error, disconnect the cables linked
         to the X124, X126, X128 and X106 one by one in order to verify if
         the error is cleared upon alarm RESET key. 


28958  10-DRIVE OFF SDM absence of power V24 INT - $SDI[112] 

       Cause:
         The 24V INT power supply for the TP and X20 modules is missing. 

       Remedy:
         Please check that an overload or a short circuit is not present.
         Disconnect all  X103A, X103B, X103C and X110 connectors one by one
         in order to verify if the error is cleared upon alarm RESET key. 


28959  10-DRIVE OFF SDM 8A power overload V24 I/O-SAFE - $SDI[113] 

       Cause:
         An overload or a short circuit occurs on the 24V I/O or 24V SAFE
         suppliers dedicated to the multibus cable and to applications. 

       Remedy:
         Please check if the error occurs during the DRIVE ON phase; in this
         case the overload/short circuit is on the 24V SAFE BRANCH. If the
         error also occurs in DRIVE OFF, the overload/shortcircuit is on the
         24V I/O branch. Please disconnect the cables linked to X124, X126,
         X128 and X106 connectors one by one in order to verify if the error
         is cleared upon alarm RESET key. 


28960  10-DRIVE OFF SDM 5A power overload V24 INT - $SDI[114] 

       Cause:
         An overload or a short circuit occurs on the 24V branch dedicated
         to supply the TP and the X20 modules. 

       Remedy:
         Disconnect, one by one, X103A, X103B, X103C connectors inside the
         cabinet and X70, X91, X92 on the robot in order to check if the
         error is cleared by pressing the alarm RESET key. 


28961  2-WARNING SDM Battery UPS charged - $SDI[117] 

       Cause:
         The UPS battery reached a charge greater than 85%. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message. 


28962  4-PAUSE SDM Battery UPS to be replaced - $SDI[119] 

       Cause:
         The UPS battery has to be replaced. 

       Remedy:
         Replace soon the UPS battery. Use the shutdown command before
         switching the controller off in order to avoid loosing the
         situation of programs. 


28963  2-WARNING ACOPOS in LOAD/Startup phase 


28964  10-DRIVE OFF SDM - $SDI[33-36] stop controlled time in conflict
       with the configuration - (%d ms.) 

       Cause:
         The stopping time in category 1 selected on SW1 and SW2 switches 
         on the SDM module is not consistent with the one required by the
         robot configuration. 

       Remedy:
         Please set the proper time by checking it on the manual of the
         robot. The standard time is 1,5s which corresponds to number 3 on
         both switches. 


28965  10-DRIVE OFF Robot local stop - $SDI[120] 

       Cause:
         The local emergency stop button has been pressed on this
         controller. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. 


28966  10-DRIVE OFF SDM Enable 2 output in short circuit - $SDI[89] 

       Cause:
         The self-diagnosis of the Enable 2 output detected a failure or a
         connection error which disallows the switching OFF of the output
         (voltage lowed than 2,5V in OFF state). 

       Remedy:
         Please check the cabling of ausiliary axes eventually present,
         disconnect X108 and X109 connectors and execute a switching off/on
         of the system in order to verify faster as possible if the voltage
         comes from outside of the SDM module or if there is a failure in
         the output circuits of the module. 


28967  10-DRIVE OFF SDM Output test KO - $SDI[90] 

       Cause:
         The SDM autotest detected a connection failure or error  which
         disallows the switching off of the outputs during the test. 

       Remedy:
         Eventually disconnect the cables on the X10 connector and check if
         the indication disappears. 


28968  10-DRIVE OFF SDM fault ERM1 module -$SDI[91] 

       Cause:
         An anomaly has been detected in the commands/states of the relay
         module for the repetition of some safety signals. 

       Remedy:
         Switch the controller off and on and check  if the message occurs
         again upon power on. In this case replace the ERM1 module and/or
         the flat connection cable. In case the indication only appears in
         some cases during the module relay commutation, check that the
         firmware version of the SDM module is greater or equal to 3.7. 


28969  10-DRIVE OFF SDM fault ERM2 module - $SDI[92] 

       Cause:
         An anomaly has been detected in the commands/states of the relay
         module for the repetition of some safety signals. 

       Remedy:
         Switch the controller off and on and check  if the message occurs
         again upon power on. In this case replace the ERM2 module and/or
         the flat connection cable. In case the indication only appears in
         some cases during the module relay commutation, check that the
         firmware version of the SDM module is greater or equal to 3.7. 


28970  10-DRIVE OFF SDM Startup Self Test KO - $SDI[93] 

       Cause:
         The SDM detected a failure during the initial tests of itself. 

       Remedy:
         Please replace the SDM module. 


28971  10-DRIVE OFF SDM Wireless Stop Repeater KO - $SDI[94] 

       Cause:
         The SDM detected a failure of the internal relay dedicated to the
         repetition of the STOP button of the wireless TP. 

       Remedy:
         Switch the controller off and on in order to execute a cycle of
         initial selftests. In the indication persists, please replace the
         SDM module. 


28972  10-DRIVE OFF SDM Cpu Mismatch - $SDI[95] 

       Cause:
         The SDM detected an error of incongruity between the two
         microcontrollers which execute the safety program. 

       Remedy:
         Switch the controller off and on in order to execute a cycle of
         initial self tests. If the indication persists, please replace the
         SDM module. 


28973  10-DRIVE OFF SDM Watchdog - $SDI[96] 

       Cause:
         The SDM detected an error during the self-diagnosis of the internal
         watchdog circuit. 

       Remedy:
         Switch the controller off and on in order to execute a cycle of
         initial selftests. If the indication persists, please replace the
         SDM module. 


28974  2-WARNING Safety frame transmission stopped 

       Cause:
         Safety frame transmission stopped. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. 


28975  2-WARNING Safety frame transmission started 

       Cause:
         Safety frame transmission started. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. 


28976  2-WARNING Forced unpairing failed because communication still
       present 

       Cause:
         Forced unpairing failed. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. 


28977  2-WARNING Forced unpairing failed because not in program state 

       Cause:
         Forced unpairing failed. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. 


28978  2-WARNING Press emergency stop request 

       Cause:
         This is an informational message. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. 


28979  2-WARNING Release emergency stop request 

       Cause:
         This is an informational message. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. 


28980  2-WARNING Forced unpairing failed 

       Cause:
         Forced unpairing failed. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. 


28981  10-DRIVE OFF X119/SDM  Brake releasing Device Cable connection
       error 

       Cause:
         Not present or wrong connector. 

       Remedy:
         Check jumper between pin 5 and pin 10 of  X119 connector. 


28982  10-DRIVE OFF X108/SDM Enable Cable connection error 

       Cause:
         The connector is not present or is wrong. 

       Remedy:
         Please verify the jumper between pin 1 and pin 6 of  X108
         connector. 


28983  2-WARNING Place the TP on the Docking Station of the Controller to
       pair 

       Cause:
         The TP is not paired to a controller and is not positioned on the
         Docking Station. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message.  For using the TP , it is needed
         to perform the pairing procedure with the TP positioned on the
         docking station. If on the contrary  this message is received when
         the TP is positioned on the docking station, this means that the
         robot controller is not powered or in fault: check in this case the
         robot controller state. 


28984  2-WARNING The controller isn't ready for pairing 

       Cause:
         The TP is positioned on the robot controller docking station, but 
         this is not able to accept pairing requests. 

       Remedy:
         If this error occurs when the TP is positioned on the docking
         station, it means that the robot controller is in an alarm state.
         Check the controller state, trying to connect to it via the WinC5G
         software. 


28985  4-PAUSE Pairing unavailable: the controller is already paired with
       another TP 

       Cause:
         The TP is positioned on the docking station of a robot controller
         which is paired to another TP. 

       Remedy:
         This message can be simply due to a user  mistake who positioned
         the TP on the docking station of the wrong controller. If, on the
         contrary, the purpose is to pair this terminal with that robot
         controller, it is needed to un-pair  the TP which is currently
         paired to such controller. Sometimes it is also needed to perform
         the emergency un-pairing procedure. 


28986  4-PAUSE The connection device isn't ready 

       Cause:
         The pairing procedure failed due to the fact that the AP (access
         point) of the TP which  is not ready yet. 

       Remedy:
         Please wait that the communication device becomes available again
         and retry. 


28987  2-WARNING Disconnecting from the robot controller 

       Cause:
         This error occurs when the pairing procedure fails. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. A previous attempt of pairing
         with the robot controller failed, the programming unit is returning
         to the initial state. The error which prevents the pairing is
         shoown during the procedure itself. 


28988  2-WARNING Resetting connection variables 

       Cause:
         This error occurs when the pairing procedure fails. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. A previous attempt of pairing
         with the robot controller failed, the programming unit is returning
         to the initial state. The error which prevents the pairing is
         shoown during the procedure itself. 


28989  2-WARNING The TP is placed in the Docking Station of a Controller
       different from the one it is paired with 

       Cause:
         The TP is positioned on the Docking Station of the controller which
         is not the one which the TP is paired with. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. Please remove the TP from the
         docking station and, if needed, position it on the docking station
         of the right controller. 


28990  2-WARNING Wait the request to push the pairing button and let the
       Controller on and the TP on the Docking station during the procedure 

       Cause:
         This condition can occur upon the pairing button pressure: before
         the TP detects the Docking station  presence; after the removal of
         the TP from the Docking station; after other abnormal
         operations/events occurred during the pairing procedure. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational  message. Please perform the pairing
         procedure as indicated on the manual. 


28991  4-PAUSE The connection device on TP cannot be reached 

       Cause:
         The TP connection device cannot be reached and the TP cannot be
         connected and paired to a robot controller. 

       Remedy:
         Try to restart the programming unit. If the problem persist, please
         contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). If, when the error
         occurred, the terminal was already paired, it could be needed to
         perform, on the robot controller, the emergency un-pairing in order
         to use a different teminal.. 


28992  4-PAUSE The Access Point isn't working properly 

       Cause:
         The TP connection device does not properly reply to the software. 

       Remedy:
         Try switching off or restarting the programming unit. If the
         problem persist , please contact COMAU
         (service.robotics@comau.com). 


28993  4-PAUSE TPSM device isn't working properly 

       Cause:
         The TPSM does not properly work. 

       Remedy:
         Try switching off or restarting the programming unit. 


28994  4-PAUSE Unknown status 

       Cause:
         Anomalous pairing. 

       Remedy:
         Try switching off or restarting the programming unit and /or
         restarting the controller. 


28995  4-PAUSE Check control unit state  and its connections to the teach
       pendant 

       Cause:
         This condition can occur upon: a failure of a ping toward the
         controller; a failure of a CEDP System connection; a failure of a
         CEDP User connection; a DPRO Timeout. 

       Remedy:
         Check the state of the controller unit and the related connections
         towards the terminal. 


28996  10-DRIVE OFF RoboSAFE - Cat 1 STOP 

       Cause:
         RoboSAFE functions executed a category 1 stop of the robot. One or
         more RoboSAFE programmed limits (position, speed) are exceeded. 

       Remedy:
         Check subsequent errors to find out the limits that are exceeded
         and that cause the robot stop. 


28997  11-DRIVE OFF RoboSAFE - Cat 0 STOP 

       Cause:
         RoboSAFE functions executed a category 0 stop of the robot. One or
         more RoboSAFE programmed limits (position, speed) are exceeded. 

       Remedy:
         Check subsequent errors to find out the limits that are exceeded
         and that cause the robot stop. 


28998  10-DRIVE OFF RS - Safe function not recovered 

       Cause:
         One or more safe functions (typically position limits) are still in
         violation state and have not yet been recovered. 

       Remedy:
         Check subsequent errors to find out which RoboSAFE function is
         still in error and perform the recovery procedures (e.g. move robot
         out of forbidden zone). 


28999  10-DRIVE OFF RS - Position communication error (SAFE LINE UP
       required) 

       Cause:
         Error on safe positions occurred during communication cycle. 

       Remedy:
         SAFE LINE UP operation following the procedure written into the
         manual is needed to recover safe position. Check status of the safe
         components (Encoders, Drives, Safe Logic) by looking other
         simultaneous errors in the error list. If the problem persists
         contact Comau service. 


29000  11-DRIVE OFF RS - Safe Logic PROG state mismatch 

       Cause:
         The programming state, checked by Safe Logic, detected an anomaly
         between hardware and system software status. 

       Remedy:
         Move state selector and check that the ERM1-L module relays are
         properly working, then check connection between ERM1-L module and
         the safe I/O. 


29001  11-DRIVE OFF RS - Robot configuration mismatch <param> 

       Cause:
         Robot description file loaded into C5G control doesn't match  with
         RoboSAFE robot parameters or the RoboSAFE software version is older
         than C5G software release. Check for exchanged component (C.F
         and/or SafeKey) between already initialized C5G controls, or for
         software reloading procedure not completed properly. 

       Remedy:
         Perform software reloading procedure (system and TP, fully reload)
         and RoboSAFE initialization procedure. If the problem persists,
         also after the software reloading, contact Comau service. 


29002  11-DRIVE OFF RS - Safe modules initialization or communication
       error 

       Cause:
         Error occurred during initialization phase of safe modules and/or
         over PowerLink network communication. 

       Remedy:
         Check PowerLink connection and power supply of safe modules
         (driver, safe I/O and Safe Logic). If the problem persists contact
         Comau service. 


29003  11-DRIVE OFF RS - Safe IO channel wiring error 

       Cause:
         Error on the wiring to safe inputs (double channel) or to safe
         outputs. 

       Remedy:
         Check the connection to safe I/O modules (mismatch over double
         channel inputs or short circuit over outputs and/or pulsed signal). 


29004  11-DRIVE OFF RS - Position diagnostic error (SAFE LINE UP required
       0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         Anomaly has been detected by start-up diagnostic on safe position.
         The <param> shows axis mask. 

       Remedy:
         SAFE LINE UP operation following the procedure written into the
         manual is needed to recover safe position. Check status of the safe
         components (Encoders, Drives, Safe Logic) by looking other
         simultaneous errors in the error list. If the problem persists
         contact Comau service. 


29005  11-DRIVE OFF RS - SS1 error on Ax <param> 

       Cause:
         Axis <param> didn't respect safe category 1 deceleration ramp
         scheduled in case of RoboSAFE functions violation. Axis <param> is
         stopped with category 0. 

       Remedy:
         Check status of the safe components (Encoders, Drives, Safe Logic)
         by looking other simultaneous errors in the error list. Contact
         Comau service to check the parameterization of the safe robot with
         implemented application. 


29006  4-PAUSE RS - Joint Space Limiting SET <param> violated 

       Cause:
         The robot has violated one or more safe joint space into SET
         <param> of Joint Space Limiting functions. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the working cycle of the robot complies with the safe
         active zone and other safety devices (e.g. laser scanner) that
         activate forbidden zone while operator presence in the robot area. 


29007  4-PAUSE RS - Joint Speed Limiting <param> violated 

       Cause:
         The robot has violated safe speed joint limit of Joint Speed
         Limiting function. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the working cycle of the robot complies with active safe
         joint speed limit. 


29008  4-PAUSE RS - TCP Speed Limiting <param> violated 

       Cause:
         The robot has violated TCP Speed Limiting <param> with one of the
         kinematic links or active tool points. 

       Remedy:
         Check that movement of the robot working cycle complies with active
         TCP Speed Limiting. Check also singularity movements. 


29009  4-PAUSE RS - Movement stop due to safe reduced speed exceeded 

       Cause:
         The robot has violated reduced speed limit (TCP) during manual
         movement with one of the kinematic links or active tool points. 

       Remedy:
         Reduce speed override and avoid movement through singularity. 


29010  2-WARNING RS - Joint Space Limiting SET <param1> activation:
       <param2> 

       Cause:
         Informational message about RoboSAFE function activation by safe
         inputs. The <param2> that could be "TRUE" or "FALSE" shows the
         status. 


29011  2-WARNING RS - Joint Speed Limiting <param1> activation: <param2> 

       Cause:
         Informational message about RoboSAFE function activation by safe
         inputs. The <param> that could be "TRUE" or "FALSE" shows the
         status. 


29012  2-WARNING RS - TCP Speed Limiting <param1> activation: <param2> 

       Cause:

         inputs. The <param2> that could be "TRUE" or "FALSE" shows the
         status. 


29013  2-WARNING RS - Safe tool <param1> point activation: <param2> 

       Cause:
         Informational message about RoboSAFE function activation by safe
         inputs. The <param2> that could be "TRUE" or "FALSE" shows the
         status. 


29014  4-PAUSE RS - RECOVERY MODE still active 

       Cause:
         RECOVERY MODE is active for more than 10 minutes. ATTENTION: all
         safe functions are disabled till the completion of the procedure. 

       Remedy:
         Complete SAFE LINE UP procedure by deactivating the command on
         RoboSAFE interface. 


29015  2-WARNING RS - Axis <param1> Arm <param2> (29004) diagnostic data
       C3: <param3> - C1: <param4> 

       Cause:
         Diagnostic data of error code 29004. View cause of error code
         29004. 

       Remedy:
         View remedy of error code 29004. 


29016  4-PAUSE RS - Cartesian Space Limiting SET <param> violated 

       Cause:
         The robot has violated one or more safe cartesian space into SET
         <param> of Cartesian Space Limiting functions. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the working cycle of the robot complies with the safe
         active zone and other safety devices (e.g. laser scanner) that
         activate forbidden zone while operator presence in the robot area. 


29017  4-PAUSE RS - Cartesian Cell Limiting violated 

       Cause:
         The robot has violated one or more safe cartesian space into the
         definition of robot working cell. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the working cycle of the robot complies with the safe
         cell definition, set and activated by web-server. 


29018  4-PAUSE RS - TCP Speed Limiting in Cartesian Space SET <param>
       violated 

       Cause:
         The robot has violated safe TCP Speed Limit related to SET <param>
         with one of the kinematic links or active tool points. 

       Remedy:
         Check that movement of the robot working cycle complies with active
         TCP Speed Limits. Check also singularity movements. 


29019  2-WARNING RS - Cartesian Space Limiting SET <param1> activation:
       <param2> 

       Cause:
         Informational message about RoboSAFE function activation by safe
         inputs. The <param2> that could be "TRUE" or "FALSE" shows the
         status. 


29020  2-WARNING RS - Cartesian Cell Limiting activation: <param1>

       failure request

         from this situation when a new power failure request has already
         been received.

29696  0-INFO Not enough window space 

       Cause:
         There are too many display command windows active on screen. 

       Remedy:
         Close one or more windows that you do not need at the same time. 


29697  0-INFO Too many parameter 

       Cause:
         More parameters were specified than required in display command. 

       Remedy:
         Check the command and remove extra parameter(s). 


29698  0-INFO Bad start of range 

       Cause:
         The start of range value (eg: 1..5) is not a valid value. 

       Remedy:
         Check if the start value is bigger than the stop value or an
         out-of-range number. 


29699  0-INFO Bad end of range 

       Cause:
         The stop of range value (eg: 1..5) is an invalid value. 

       Remedy:
         Check if the stop value is smaller than the start value or an
         out-of-range number. 


29700  0-INFO Range too large 

       Cause:
         The range specified is too large to fit into the display window. 

       Remedy:
         Split the range into more groups and specify one at a time. 


29701  0-INFO Invalid parameter 

       Cause:
         An invalid parameter was specified in a display command. 

       Remedy:
         Check the manual to determine the proper parameter specification
         for that command. 


29702  0-INFO CURSOR DOWN:select;ENTER:close;PREV:end 

       Cause:
         This is an help message to describe how to move on windows open in
         the Display command. The down arrow key moves the focus on the
         different open windows; the ENTER key closes the window; the PREV
         key exists from windows selection. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message. 


29703  0-INFO Program already displayed 

       Cause:
         The program is already displayed in a display window. 

       Remedy:
         Check the current display windows for the program. 


29704  0-INFO Bad arm number 

       Cause:
         Invalid arm number specification in a DISPLAY command requiring an
         arm number. 

       Remedy:
         Check to see if the arm exists. 


29705  0-INFO 


29706  0-INFO No display active 

       Cause:
         The DISPLAY CLOSE SELECT (DCS) command was issued without any
         active display windows on the screen or all active displays have
         just been closed. 

       Remedy:
         There is not a problem, the command automatically terminates
         because there are no active display windows. 


29707  0-INFO 


29708  0-INFO 


29709  0-INFO Bad sysvar display period 

       Cause:
         The predefined variable $TUNE[15] has a value that is out of range.
         The valid range is from 30 to 60000 milliseconds.  If an invalid
         value is specified, the default time of 1000 ms is used. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the value of the predefined variable $TUNE[15] is within
         the valid range. 


29710  0-INFO Bad sysvar CRT display max lines 

       Cause:
         The predefined variable $TUNE[16] has a value that is out of range.
         The valid range is from 0 to 16 lines.  If an invalid value is
         specified, the default of 16 lines is used. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the value of the predefined variable $TUNE[16] is within
         the valid range. 


29711  0-INFO Display commands disabled 

       Cause:
         One of the DISPLAY group of commands has been issued when the
         $TUNE[15] value was set to 0, that means that the commands of this
         group are disabled. 

       Remedy:
         Set the value of $TUNE[15] to 1000, for enabling the DISPLAY
         refresh every second. 


29712  0-INFO Bad sysvar TP display max lines 

       Cause:
         The predefined variable $TUNE[17] has a value that is out of range.
         The valid range is from 0 to 10 lines.  If an invalid value is
         specified, the default of 10 lines is used. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the value of the predefined variable $TUNE[17] is within
         the valid range. 


29713  0-INFO Bad separator, use '-' or '..' 

       Cause:
         An invalid separator was used in the parameter string. 

       Remedy:
         Use a valid separator which is '..' for ranges and '-' for single
         numbers. 


29714  0-INFO Invalid parameter character 

       Cause:
         An invalid character was used in the parameter string. 

       Remedy:
         Check the parameter syntax in the manual. 


29715  0-INFO Two Arm windows already active; close one 

       Cause:
         The DISPLAY ARM (DA) command can work only on two windows at the
         same time. A DISPLAY ARM command was issued on another arm number
         with two arm windows already active. 

       Remedy:
         Close one of the arm windows with the DISPLAY CLOSE SELECT (DCS)
         command or close all the arm windows with the DISPLAY CLOSE ARM
         (DCA) command before reissuing the DISPLAY ARM command. 


29716  0-INFO FBus Master boards not present 

       Cause:
         The DISPLAY FIELDBUS MASTER (DFM) command was issued without any
         Fieldbus Master boards present. 

       Remedy:
         There is not a problem, the command automatically terminates. 


29717  0-INFO FBus Slave boards not present 

       Cause:
         The DISPLAY FIELDBUS SLAVE (DFS) command was issued without any
         Fieldbus Master boards present. 

       Remedy:
         There is not a problem, the command automatically terminates. 


29718  0-INFO 


29719  0-INFO 


29720  0-INFO

30201  0-INFO SYSTEM ERROR: Error calling hs_qident: %d
