48672  10-DRIVE OFF <<device_name>> offline (<diagnostic_code>) 

       Cause:
         The indicated device is not connected to the system. Here follows
         the list of possible causes and remedies depending on the
         <diagnostic code>: ***<<0>> No error. ***<<1>> Missing node
         (device). The device stopped running. Check if device is still
         switched on and connected. ***<<2>> The device has been stopped
         (Device). ***<<30>> Device timeout (Device). The device stopped
         communicating. Check the baudrate and the MAC-ID. ***<<32>> The
         device replied with an unknown system error. (Device) ***<<35>>
         Connection error during the allocation phase. (Device) ***<<36>>
         Number of inputs of the device different from what configured.
         (Device / configuration) ***<<37>> Number of outputs of the device
         different from what configured. (Device / configuration) ***<<38>>
         Unknown response from device.(Device) ***<<39>> Device already
         connected. (Device) The connection will be automatically released.
         ***<<40>> The device is in conflict with the DeviceNet protocol.
         (Device) ***<<41>> The device is already connected to the
         master.(Device / Hilscher master device) ***<<42>> Length of the
         polling device response differs from what declared. (Device)
         ***<<43>> Error detected while reading data in polling. (Device)
         ***<<44>> Error detected while reading data in polling. (Device)
         ***<<45>> Error detected while reading data in polling. (Device)
         ***<<46>> Error detected while reading data in bit strobe. (Device)
         ***<<47>> Error detected while reading data in COS or ciclic.
         (Device) ***<<48>> Error detected while reading data in COS or
         ciclic. (Device) ***<<49>> Error detected while reading data in COS
         or ciclic. (Device) ***<<50>> Error detected while reading data in
         COS or ciclic. (Device) ***<<51>> UCMM group not supported
         (Device). Change the UCMM group. ***<<52>> Error during the check
         of the Device Keying. Vendor ID mismatch (Device / configuration).
         Check the configured Vendor ID against the device Vendor ID.
         ***<<52>> Error during the check of the Device Keying. Vendor ID
         mismatch (Device / configuration). Check the configured Vendor ID
         against the device Vendor ID. ***<<53>> Error during the check of
         the Device Keying. Device Type (Device / configuration). Check the
         configured Device Type against the Device Type of the device .
         ***<<54>> Error during the check of the Device Keying. Product code
         mismatch (Device / configuration). Check the configured Product
         Code against the Product Code of the device. ***<<55>> Error during
         the check of the Device Keying. Revision mismatch (Device /
         configuration). Check the configured Revision against the Revision
         of the device. ***<<59>> Multiple devices have the same address on
         the network. (Configuration) Each DeviceNet device must have its
         own MACID. ***<<60>> Error reading the database. (Configuration)
         Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com) ***<<61>> Error
         reading the database. (Configuration) Please contact COMAU
         (service.robotics@comau.com) ***<<62>> Error reading the database.
         (Configuration) Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com)
         ***<<63>> Error reading the database. (Configuration) Please
         contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com) ***<<64>> Internal
         error. (Configuration) Please contact COMAU
         (service.robotics@comau.com) ***<<65>> Internal error.
         (Configuration) Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com)
         ***<<66>> Internal error. (Configuration) Please contact COMAU
         (service.robotics@comau.com) ***<<67>> Internal error.
         (Configuration) Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com)
         ***<<68>> Internal error. (Configuration) Please contact COMAU
         (service.robotics@comau.com) ***<<69>> Internal error.
         (Configuration) Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com)
         ***<<70>> Internal error. (Configuration) Please contact COMAU
         (service.robotics@comau.com) ***<<71>> Internal error.
         (Configuration) Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com)
         ***<<72>> Internal error. (Configuration) Please contact COMAU
         (service.robotics@comau.com) ***<<73>> Internal error.
         (Configuration) Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com) 

       Remedy:
         Please read the listed above causes and remedies associated to the
         <diagnostic_code>. 


48673  8-HOLD <device_name>: slot <slot> not initialized 

       Cause:
         The master/slave network has not been activated because the
         Powerlink module for handling the fieldbus interface has not been
         initialized. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the Powerlink device is declared. 


48674  10-DRIVE OFF No Data Base found (<network>) 

       Cause:
         The DeviceNet Master couldn't load the data base for the network
         configuration. Usually this message is associated to a series of
         messages indicating that all other devices on the network are
         offline. 

       Remedy:
         This could be due to: the missing of the network configuration file
         or to a malfunction to the X20BC1083 module. Check the presence of
         file 42764b1.fw.gz file in LD:\EPL or replace the X20BC1083 module. 


48675  0-INFO <master_name> active, device/s: <device_num> 

       Cause:
         The indicated Master is active and it is handling the specified
         total amount of devices. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message only. 


48676  2-WARNING <<device_name>> connected 

       Cause:
         The specified device is connected and is properly exchanging the
         I/O data. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message only. 


48677  10-DRIVE OFF <<device_name>> not connected 

       Cause:
         The specified device is not connected to the system. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the device is physically connected to the system. Check
         that the device is properly configured. 


48678  2-WARNING <<device_name>> disabled 

       Cause:
         The specified device has been disabled. 

       Remedy:
         The specified device can now be disconnected from the net. 


48679  10-DRIVE OFF <master_name>: no devices on the net 

       Cause:
         The Master is active on its net, but it couldn't find any devices
         among the ones specified in the expected configuration. 

       Remedy:
         Check the presence of the devices on the net and whether they
         correspond to the expected addresses in the configuration. 


48680  10-DRIVE OFF <master_name>: there is at least one not connected
       device 

       Cause:
         The Master is active on its net, but at least one of the expected
         devices in the configuration, is not connected. 

       Remedy:
         Check the presence of the devices on the net and whether they
         correspond to the expected addresses in the configuration. 


48681  10-DRIVE OFF <<master_name>> 24VDC not present 

       Cause:
         The power supply on the specified Master net is not available. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the voltage is present on the bus. Check that the cable
         is connected to the Master interface. Check the status of the front
         LEDs  of the Master interface. 


48682  10-DRIVE OFF <<device_name>> 24VDC not present 

       Cause:
         The power supply on the specified device is not available. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the voltage is present on the bus. Check that the cable
         is connected to the Master interface. 


48683  8-HOLD Configuration reading failure: 0x<parameter> 

       Cause:
         An error occurred while reading the configuration. 

       Remedy:
         Execute again the I/O configuration tool. 


48684  8-HOLD Memory allocation failure 

       Cause:
         An error occurred  while reading the configuration. 

       Remedy:
         Reboot the system. 


48685  8-HOLD Too many first level elements 

       Cause:
         Too many first level elements have been added to the configuration
         tree. 

       Remedy:
         Be sure there is one first level element only.

       Cause:
         The specified mandatory field has not been found in the current
         type. 

       Remedy:
         Check the correctness of the variable type.

         Check that the address belongs to the allowed range of the
         protocol.

52736  8-HOLD BSBUFLIB: wrong idpool parameter 

       Cause:
         The idpool input parameter of the function library is not allowed. 

       Remedy:
         Contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


52737  8-HOLD BSBUFLIB: buffer not owned by the caller 

       Cause:
         The processor that requested the buffer is not the owner of any
         buffer in the selected pool. 

       Remedy:
         Contact COMAU(service.robotics@comau.com). 


52738  8-HOLD BSBUFLIB: caller not allowed 

       Cause:
         The calling processor is not handled by the system or required the
         sending of a buffer to itself. 

       Remedy:
         Contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


52739  8-HOLD BSBUFLIB: caller is not the System Master 

       Cause:
         The library function can only be called by the System Master Board. 

       Remedy:
         Contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


52740  8-HOLD BSBUFLIB: no memory for pool of buffers 

       Cause:
         There is no more available memory for creating another pool of
         buffers. 

       Remedy:
         Contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


52741  8-HOLD BSBUFLIB: no input buffers 

       Cause:
         The calling processor is not the destination of any buffer. 

       Remedy:
         Contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com).

       Cause:
         The parameter related to the CPU is not allowed or the number of
         the calling CPU is not allowed. 

       Remedy:
         Contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


52743  8-HOLD BSCPULIB: timeout for bsfi_syncWait 

       Cause:
         The waiting for a signal from another CPU timed out. 

       Remedy:
         Contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


52744  8-HOLD BSCPULIB: bad parameters in bsfi_syncRendezVous 

       Cause:
         Either the input parameters  to the function are wrong (the value
         of pointers is NULL) or the calling CPU is not one of the allowed
         ones. 

       Remedy:
         Contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


52745  8-HOLD BSCPULIB: timeout during bsfi_syncRendezVous 

       Cause:
         The waiting for a signal from other CPUs during the
         bsfi_syncRendezVous timed out. 

       Remedy:
         Contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com).

52778  8-HOLD RPU run-down battery 

       Cause:
         The battery of the RPU rack run-down. It's status is checked any
         time in which the controller is switched on and it is also checked
         every 5 seconds. 

       Remedy:
         If the controller has been switched off many consecutive times, the
         battery needs a time for totally recovering the power and it is
         suggested to maintain the controller switched on for at least 16
         hours in order to allowe the restore. Otherwise it is suggested to
         replace the battery, due to the usury of it, in order to correctly
         recover the system after a power down. Please verify the efficiency
         of the battery with the procedure described in the maintenance
         manual.

       Remedy:
         Check that the memory being adressed matches with a correct page.

       Cause:
         A not existing page of memory has been referenced. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the memory being adressed matches with a correct page.

54295  0-INFO 


54296  10-DRIVE OFF Node <address>, output(s) not active 

       Cause:
         The outputs linked to the node are set in a not active state. This
         occurs when a short circuit is detected on one ore more outputs.
         The outputs are set in the not active state in order to preserve
         the integrity of circuits. 

       Remedy:
         Verify what caused the short circuit. After having restored the
         controller from the alarm generated by the short circuit, the node
         is activated again. If the short circuit has not been removed, the
         alarm is restored again.

54573  10-DRIVE OFF Node <address>, short circuit on output(s) 

       Cause:
         The node signals the presence of a short circuit on one output. 

       Remedy:
         Remove the short circuit. 


54574  2-WARNING Node <address>, restore from short circuit 

       Cause:
         Upon a short circuit the node disables its outputs in order to
         remove the short circuit output alarm. This is done in order to
         remove the alarm generation until the cause of the problem has been
         removed. The node will be re-enabled after a reset on alarms and
         /or a disconnection from the CAN bus or after the switching off of
         the node. The conditions for detecting the presence of a short
         circuit are enabled after the node restart. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message. 


54575  2-WARNING Node <address>, Bus Off state 

       Cause:
         The node signals the impossibility of occessing to the CAN bus. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the CAN Cable is not in short circuit. 


54576  2-WARNING Node <address>, restore from Bus Off 

       Cause:
         The node signals the restore of the communication on CAN bus. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message. 


54577  2-WARNING Node <address>, Watch dog timeout 

       Cause:
         The node signals that the continuous check on activities with the
         system board has expired. This problem could be caused by the
         hanging of system board for some reason. 

       Remedy:
         If the system board works, check the CAN bus cable. 


54578  2-WARNING Node <address>, Watch dog restore 

       Cause:
         The synchronization with the system board has been restored. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message. 


54579  2-WARNING Node <address>, transmission queue full 

       Cause:
         A secondary channel of the switch cannot transmit messages on CAN. 

       Remedy:
         Please check the connections to secondary channels. 


54580  2-WARNING Node <address>, restore of transmission 

       Cause:
         The secondary channel of the switch is correctly transmitting
         messages. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message. 


54581  2-WARNING Node <address>, low quality of transmission 

       Cause:
         A secondary channel of the switch is generating many transmission
         errors. 

       Remedy:
         Please check the connections to the secondary channels. 


54582  2-WARNING Node <address>, regular quality of transmission 

       Cause:
         The secondary channel associated to the switch is correctly
         transmitting messages. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message.

       Remedy:

57347  14-FATAL Arm <arm_num> $RB_VARIANT mismatch 

       Cause:
         A mismatch has been detected in the values present in $RB_VARIANT
         related to the acceleration algorithm and the kind of robot. 

       Remedy:
         Please report this error to COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


57348  0-INFO 


57349  2-WARNING CPU: <servo_num> wrong value for $CT_JNT_MASK 

       Cause:
         The axis involved in $CONV_TBL[i].CT_JNT_MASK (where 'i' is 1 or 2)
         is not allowed to be an external position transducer because it is
         already linked to a predefined arm. As a consequence the system
         variable has been ignored and set to the zero value; the conveyor
         tracking/reading is not yet configured. 

       Remedy:
         Check the correct value for the $CONV_TBL[i].CT_JNT_MASK. Remember
         that the mask must consider the phisical channel of the axis linked
         to the external position transducer used for the conveyor tracking. 


57350  0-INFO 


57351  0-INFO 


57352  2-WARNING Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> $CAL_DATA not valid 

       Cause:
         Calibration constants that have been saved in the retentive memory
         are not valid, out of range or numerically wrong (NAN, INF). In
         case of command CARL_Motor, possible inconsistency with
         $ARM_DATA[].ARM_ID not valid. 

       Remedy:
         For initializing calibration constants it is needed to execute the
         calibration of the axis involved.

57361  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> auxiliary axis not
       configured

         The auxiliary axis is not configured correctly. 

       Remedy:

         checking that the type of axis (X,Y,Z) is explicitly declared. 


57362  11-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> arm MASTER not correctly configured 

       Cause:
         The MASTER arm for the Axes Pursuit option is not configured
         correctly. 

       Remedy:
         Configure the MASTER arm with the variable $AX_PURSUIT_ARM_MASTER,
         and be sure that its value is consistent. 


57363  11-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> arm SLAVE not correctly configured 

       Cause:
         The SLAVE arm for the Axes Pursuit option is not configured
         correctly. 

       Remedy:
         Configure the SLAVE arm with the variable $AX_PURSUIT_LINKED, and
         be sure that its value is consistent (es.
         $ARM_DATA[2].AX_PURSUIT_LINKED[1] := 7). 


57364  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> the axes of MASTER arm
       does not exist 

       Cause:
         The axes of the MASTER arm for the Axes Pursuit option does not
         exist. 

       Remedy:
         Be sure that the variables $AX_PURSUIT_LINKED have been set with a
         correct value for the axes for the MASTER arm (ex.
         $ARM_DATA[2].AX_PURSUIT_LINKED[1] := 7, axes 7 must exist on the
         MASTER arm). 


57365  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> the axes of SLAVE arm
       does not exist 

       Cause:
         The axes of the SLAVE arm for the Axes Pursuit option does not
         exist. 

       Remedy:
         Be sure that the variables $AX_PURSUIT_LINKED have been set with a
         correct value for the axes for the SLAVE arm (ex.
         $ARM_DATA[2].AX_PURSUIT_LINKED[1] := 7, axes 2 must exist on the
         SLAVE arm). 


57366  11-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> More than one SLAVE arm is configured 

       Cause:
         The system includes more than one SLAVE arm; the inconsistency does
         not allow the system with Axes Pursuit function enabled to work
         correctly. 

       Remedy:
         Control that the variables $AX_PURSUIT_LINKED are correctly
         configured for one SLAVE arm (ex. the following configuration:
         $ARM_DATA[2].AX_PURSUIT_LINKED[1] := 7 and
         $ARM_DATA[3].AX_PURSUIT_LINKED[2] := 3 is not correct as it is
         declaring arm 2 and arm 3 as SLAVE arms, but for Axes Pursuit
         option it only one SLAVE arm per time is possible. 


57367  11-DRIVE OFF ACP node <node>  not connected 

       Cause:
         The specified device is not connected to the system. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the device is physically connected to the system. Check
         that the device is properly configured. The cause  might derive
         from the upstream device which, interrupting the communication on
         the Powerlink, could cause connection problems. 


57368  11-DRIVE OFF ACP node <node> connected 

       Cause:
         The specified device is connected and is properly exchanging the
         data. 

       Remedy:
         This is an informational message only. 


57369  11-DRIVE OFF ACP EPL Network Error: %s %ld 


57370  11-DRIVE OFF The application in $TRK_TBL[<arm_num>] does not exist 

       Cause:
         An unimplemented tracking application has been requested. 

       Remedy:
         Check the $TRK_TBL[nTbl].TT_APPL_ID variable and, eventually,
         correct the value. 


57371  11-DRIVE OFF More arms configured in $TRK_TBL[<arm_num>] 

       Cause:
         In the system more than one arm have been configured. The required
         track modality cannot properly work with this configuration. 

       Remedy:
         Verify that $TRK_TBL[nTbl].TT_ARM_MASK variable refers to a single
         arm. 


57372  11-DRIVE OFF Bad arm configuration in $TRK_TBL[<arm_num>] 

       Cause:
         Bad arm configuration in the table, the arm does not exists or is
         already configured on a different table. This missing or wrong
         parameter does notallows a proper functioning of the system. 

       Remedy:
         Check the value of the $TRK_TBL[nTbl].TT_ARM_MASK variable for the
         associated $FMI and, in case of Versamotion, that it is declared in
         a single $TRK_TBL[] table. 


57373  11-DRIVE OFF Wrong port type in $TRK_TBL[<arm_num>] 

       Cause:
         Wrong port type for the required tracking application. 

       Remedy:
         Verify and check the port type configured in the table. 


57374  11-DRIVE OFF Port <port_num> in $TRK_TBL[<tbl_num>] not present 

       Cause:
         The port for the required track application in the table has not
         been linked. 

       Remedy:
         Check if the port number is correct and has been linked. 


57375  10-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> Axis not available for
       <func_num> function 

       Cause:
         The axis configured for the function is not a robot axis. function
         1 = HDIN; 3 = STRKEND; 5 = AIR/ROBOT 

       Remedy:
         Define a robot axis for the function. 


57376  10-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> Data on NvRam mismatching with the Robot 

       Cause:
         Data read from NvRam do not match with the robot ones that are
         currectly loaded on the controller. 

       Remedy:
         Check the data in the calibration file in UD:\SYS\CNFG and, if
         correct, issue the command  for loading from retentive memory from
         the SetupArm page(CARL/F). 


57377  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> data file not compatible 

       Cause:
         The version of the data file is not compatible with the system
         software version. 

       Remedy:
         Please update the data file version. 


57378  14-FATAL Advanced modeling file not found 

       Cause:
         Advanced modeling file not found 

       Remedy:
         Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


57379  10-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> eMotion cannot be enabled 

       Cause:
         eMotion cannot be enabled on the specified arm. 

       Remedy:
         Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


57380  14-FATAL Arm <num_arm> error load characterization file 

       Cause:
         The characterization file is corrupted or not congruent. 

       Remedy:
         Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com).

58368  4-PAUSE 2nd Euler angle less than zero 

       Cause:
         For definition the second Euler angle cannot be less than 0 degrees
         or greater than 180 degrees. 

       Remedy:
         Set the angle accordingly. 


58369  2-WARNING <prog_id>(<line_num>): sensor enabled during the RUN
       Multipass phase 

       Cause:
         The predefined Multipass routine has been called for the RUN phase
         with the enabled Sensor tracking ($SENSOR_ENBL:=TRUE). 

       Remedy:
         Disable the  Sensor Tracking ($SENSOR_ENBL:=FALSE) before calling
         the predefined Multipass routine or clea the offset value for the
         Sensor Track during the RUN MultiPass phase. 


58370  2-WARNING <prog_id>(<line_num>): sensor disabled during the TEACH
       MultiPass phase 

       Cause:
         The predefined Multipass routine for the TEACH phase has been
         called while the Sensor tracking was disabled
         ($SENSOR_ENBL:=FALSE). 

       Remedy:
         Please enable the  Sensor Tracking ($SENSOR_ENBL:=TRUE) before
         calling the predefined Multipass routine or clear the offset value
         for the  Sensor Track during the TEACH MultiPass phase.

58875  0-INFO SYSTEM ERROR: Preliminary Count queue not found

58880  10-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> error upon DRIVE ON 

       Cause:
         The servo area does not recognizes a DRIVE ON request. The state is
         ALARM probably due to errors related to motors/encoder. 

       Remedy:
         Analize the errors previously displayed on the controller and reset
         the alarm state. Issue the DRIVE ON again. 


58881  10-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> axis in a state
       different from what expected (0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         It is not possible to send the command due the actual axis state.
         This is probably due to errors previously occurred and not reset. 

       Remedy:
         Analize the errors previously displayed on the controller and reset
         the alarm state. Issue the command again. 


58882  4-PAUSE Arm <arm_num> DRIVE OFF already in progress 

       Cause:
         The DRIVE OFF procedure has already been activated by another
         command or by an error condition. 

       Remedy:
         Check if errors previously occurred. 


58883  11-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> timeout for axes disabling 

       Cause:
         The DRIVE OFF procedure did not complete in the foreseen time. The
         status of some axes indicates that the procedure didn't correctly
         complete. 

       Remedy:
         Analize errors previously displayed on the controller. 


58884  11-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> timeout for drive enabling(sts:<param>) 

       Cause:
         The power activating procedure on the drive did not complete in the
         foreseen time. The drive is in the state indicated by the (sts)
         parameter associated to the message. Something avoided the bus to
         reach the required voltage. 

       Remedy:
         Analize errors previously displayed on the controller. 


58885  11-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> timeout on axes enabling
       (sts:0x<param1>-0x<param2>) 

       Cause:
         At least one axis did not complete the enabling procedure. The
         first status parameter indicates the mask of axes that are required
         to be enabled. The second status parameter indicates the mask of
         axes that successfully completed the operation. 

       Remedy:
         Analize errors previously displayed on the controller. 


58886  4-PAUSE Arm <arm_num> drive not active (sts:<param>) 

       Cause:
         The drive is no more in the active state when the command for axes
         enabling has been received. The drive state is the parameter
         associated to this error message. 

       Remedy:
         Analize errors previously displayed on the controller. 


58887  4-PAUSE Arm <arm_num> interruption of drive activation
       (sts:<param>) 

       Cause:
         The activation command has been interrupted during the first DRIVE
         ON phase. The drive state is indicated with this message. 

       Remedy:
         Analize errors previously displayed on the controller. 


58888  4-PAUSE Arm <arm_num> drive not ready for activation (sts:<param>) 

       Cause:
         The drives activation command cannot be sent because the drive is
         not in a state that allows to handle this command. 

       Remedy:
         Analize errors previously displayed on the controller. 


58889  4-PAUSE Arm <arm_num> drive not disabled (sts:<param>) 

       Cause:
         The drive disable phase did not complete in the foreseen time. The
         drive state is reported with this error message. The DRIVE OFF
         procedure completed in any case. 

       Remedy:
         Analize errors previously displayed on the controller. 


58890  11-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> timeout in calibration/turnset
       procedure(Axf: <param>) 

       Cause:
         The calibration or turn_set procedure, for axes identified by the
         "AxF" mask, did not complete in time. 

       Remedy:
         Analize the errors previously viewed on the controller. 


58891  10-DRIVE OFF Maximum power absorbed 

       Cause:
         The robot cycle time is stressing the controller which could
         overheat. One or more axes could be moving with a braked axis. 

       Remedy:
         The work cycle could overload the robot. Please change, if
         possible, the trajectory so to remove axes from an excessive
         stress. If the problem persists, it is needed to analize the robot
         ability  as far as concerns the work cycle and the system should be
         tuned accordingly to other system parameters. Verify that the
         connections to the brakes are not open.

59386  0-INFO SYSTEM ERROR: Arm %d rngBufPut errore %d

59390  0-INFO SYSTEM ERROR: Arm %d Timer activation failed 


59391  0-INFO SYSTEM ERROR: Arm %d mismatch 


59392  14-FATAL No memory available 

       Cause:
         Servo CPU system pool does not have enough available memory for the
         system software request. 

       Remedy:
         Report this error to COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com).  The user
         cannot solve this problem. 


59393  10-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> timeout on DSP driver 

       Cause:
         Handshaking with the servo control driver failed; no response from
         it after a request. The servo driver task could be aborted. 

       Remedy:
         Report this error to COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). The user
         cannot solve this problem. 


59394  8-HOLD Arm <tbl_num> not enabled for $TRK_TBL[<arm_num>] 

       Cause:
         It has been requested the enabling on an arm which is not currently
         enabled for that table element. 

       Remedy:
         Check the table configuration and the correctness of  parameters
         specified in the predefined routine. 


59395  8-HOLD Conveyor in $TRK_TBL[<tbl_num>] active on arm <arm_num> 

       Cause:
         It has been requested the initialization/enabling of a conveyor
         which is already active on the arm. 

       Remedy:
         Check the correctness of the conveyor table element to be used or
         deactivate the tracking before initializing or reactivating it. 


59396  8-HOLD Command not foreseen in CONV_TRACK routine 

       Cause:
         An uncorrect command has been required in the CONV_TRACK predefined
         routine. 

       Remedy:
         Input the correct value of the command. 


59397  10-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> servo calibration
       aborted 

       Cause:
         The servo control does not accept the theoretical position during
         the startup phase or during calibration/turn-set/JNT_SET_TAR
         operations. If the servo control is not properly reading the
         position transducer this error occurs. 

       Remedy:
         Check the position transducer circuits. If the problem persists,
         report it to COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


59398  8-HOLD Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> axis not configured 

       Cause:
         The user is trying to calibrate and/or turn-set an axes which is
         not declared for the system. 

       Remedy:
         Do not calibrate and/or turn-set an undeclared axes. 


59399  8-HOLD Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> calibration data not valid 

       Cause:
         The user is trying to turn-set an axis for which the calibration
         error is not valid. 

       Remedy:
         Analyze the history of the .C5G system data file. This file should
         contain the correct calibration error for each axes saved at
         calibration time. If it is not corrupted, load it, while drives are
         off, and reexecute the procedure. If the file was saved following
         the instructions, this axes now has a valid calibration error. If
         the file is corrupted, load the calibration error from the NVRAM,
         and reexecute the turn-set procedure. If the error does not vanish,
         the NVRAM data are also not valid. The axes need to be
         recalibrated. If the error does vanish, during the calibration
         procedure or after someone did not follow the instructions properly
         working with the system data files. 


59400  2-WARNING Arm <arm_num> attempted operation in drive off 

       Cause:
         An attempt was made to execute the calibration/turn-set operation
         when not in PROG state. 

       Remedy:
         Enter PROG state before executing the procedure. 


59401  8-HOLD Error in $TRK_TBL[<tbl_num>] parameters 

       Cause:
         The table element specified in the predefined routine has wrong
         parameters. 

       Remedy:
         Please check the table configuration and the correctness of
         parameters inside. 


59402  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> arm not calibrated 

       Cause:
         It is not possible to execute MOVE instructions when the arm is not
         calibrated. 

       Remedy:
         Calibrate or turn-set the arm before executing MOVE instructions. 


59403  8-HOLD Motion request mismatch with system state 

       Cause:
         Immediate execution MOVE statements are accepted only in PROG
         state. 

       Remedy:
         Enter PROG state before executing a MOVE statement. 


59404  8-HOLD Conveyor in $TRK_TBL[<tbl_num>] non inizialized for Arm
       <arm_num> 

       Cause:
         It has been requested to activate a conveyor which is not
         initialized yet for the Arm. 

       Remedy:
         Please check the correctness of the conveyor table to use and
         initialize the tracking before enabling it. 


59405  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> bad operation with pending motion 

       Cause:
         There are pending MOVE statements already executed by the
         interpreter but not yet executed by the interpolator when the user
         is trying to calibrate/turn-set an arm. The same message is sent
         when the AUX_COOP, ARM_COOP or ARM_SOFT built-in's are executed
         during a movement; this can happen if an ADVANCE clause is present
         on a MOVE statement before the built-in's or if built-in's are just
         at the beginning of the program (at the start of the program, a
         recovery movement is performed). 

       Remedy:
         DEACTIVATE all the programs before the calibration/turn-set
         procedure. If the message is due to the cooperation, the ADVANCE
         clause before AUX_COOP, ARM_COOP or ARM_SOFT built-in's must be
         removed. If built-in's are just at the beginning of a program they
         are to be moved down or a DELAY statement is to be introduced
         before them. 


59406  8-HOLD Conveyor in $TRK_TBL[<num_tbl>] not active on Arm <num_arm> 

       Cause:
         Required deactivation for a conveyor not active on this Arm. 

       Remedy:
         Check conveyor number to deactivate. 


59407  8-HOLD Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> $STRK_END_P out of range 

       Cause:
         The user $STRK_END_P[i] predefined variable has an absolute value
         greater than the corresponding system value $STRK_END_SYS[1][i]. 

       Remedy:
         Restrict the user stroke end. 


59408  8-HOLD Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> $STRK_END_N out of range 

       Cause:
         The user $STRK_END_N[i] predefined variable has an absolute value
         greater than the corresponding system value $STRK_END_SYS[2][i]. 

       Remedy:
         Restrict the user stroke end. 


59409  2-WARNING Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> joint position not accurate
       enough 

       Cause:
         During the turn-set procedure the user should move the arm near the
         calibration references. If the position is not so accurate, there
         could be problems due to position transducer wrap and the operation
         will fail. 

       Remedy:
         Move the arm as close as possible to the references. 


59410  8-HOLD START/BACK not available 

       Cause:
         The START/BACK keys are currently disabled.  This occurs after
         certain errors or when a manual motion is executed outside the EDIT
         environment.  The START/BACK keys only work in PROG state when the
         motion was issued from within the EDIT environment. The EDIT
         environment includes PROGRAM EDIT/DATA,  MEMORY DEBUG, immediate
         mode EXECUTE (E). 

       Remedy:
         If the keys are disabled due to an error, clear the error. 
         Otherwise, enter the EDIT environment (PROGRAM EDIT/DATA, MEMORY
         DEBUG, immediate mode EXECUTE). 


59411  8-HOLD Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> motion after last reset
       (<reason>) 

       Cause:
         The position transducer detects  a quote, at startup time,
         different than the one stored before the power down. This could be
         due to: the slipping of an axis (with or without a MOVE) during the
         powering off (<reason>=1); or to an error preceeding the switching
         off which caused the loss of the turn-set (<reason>=1); or to the
         shutdown of an axis with the system switched off (for example
         during the transportation) (<reason>=2); or to the detection, upon
         controller restart, of a conflict between the position read by the
         encoder and the one read by the device which stores the quote
         (retentive memory NVRAM) (<reason>=2). 

       Remedy:
         In case of (<reason>=1) and loss of Turn-set, please verify the
         errors which precede this one. In case of(<reason>=2)please contact
         COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). In case of problems in the
         encoder, other errors related to the encoder could be present;
         check which are these errors and it would probably be needed to
         replace the encoder. In case of problems in the NVRAM, please
         replace the APC. 


59412  2-WARNING Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> influencing axis not
       calibrated 

       Cause:
         An attempt was made to execute a turn-set operation on an axes
         which has an influence on another one and the influencing axes is
         not already calibrated. 

       Remedy:
         The influencing axes should be properly calibrated before trying to
         calibrate the influenced one. 


59413  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> interpolator already running 

       Cause:
         An attempt to execute a motion while the interpolator is already
         active was done.  The motion stack is already full, so it is no
         longer possible to stack moves other than if they are coming from
         the same program. An exeception is an immediate mode EXECUTE (E)
         MOVE.  Only one immediate mode EXECUTE (E) MOVE is accepted. 

       Remedy:
         CANCEL the motion which is active, this leaves the stacked motions
         as they are, but now it is possible to execute another motion. 


59414  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> general recovery error 

       Cause:
         It is not possible to recover the interrupted motion. Sometimes
         this could happen if the recovery is done in Cartesian and there is
         a mismatch in the configuration flags. 

       Remedy:
         Set $RCVR_TYPE in order to do the recovery in joint or if it is not
         strictly necessary to recover, DEACTIVATE or CANCEL the interrupted
         motion. 


59415  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> $RCVR_TYPE doesn't permit recovery 

       Cause:
         $RCVR_TYPE setting does not permit the recovery session. 

       Remedy:
         Set $RCVR_TYPE to a different value or if it is not necessary to
         recover anything, DEACTIVATE the program. 


59416  0-INFO 


59417  2-WARNING Already at the initial position. Line:<motion_line_num> 

       Cause:
         The user pressed the BACK button when the arm is already at the
         initial position of this segment. 

       Remedy:
         It is not possible to go backwards any further. 


59418  2-WARNING Final position reached. Line:<motion_line_num> 

       Cause:
         The arm has reached the final position. If the user releases and
         presses again the START button, the motion is completed, otherwise
         the user is still able to move backwards on this motion. 


59419  2-WARNING Initial position reached. Line:<motion_line_num> 

       Cause:
         The arm has reached the initial position and therefore cannot go
         backwards any further. The user is still able to move forwards on
         this motion. 


59420  2-WARNING Recovery position reached. Line:<motion_line_num> 

       Cause:
         The arm has reached the recovery position. If the user releases and
         presses again the START button, the next motion will start. 


59421  2-WARNING Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> positive adjustment is
       required 

       Cause:
         During the turn-set procedure the user should move the arm near the
         calibration references. The position is accurate but not so much.
         The controller is requesting the user to move the arm in the
         positive direction. 

       Remedy:
         Move the arm in the positive direction and issue the command again. 


59422  2-WARNING Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> negative adjustment is
       required 

       Cause:
         During the turn-set procedure the user should move the arm near the
         calibration references. The position is accurate but not so much.
         The controller is requesting the user to move the arm in the
         negative direction. 

       Remedy:
         Move the arm in the negative direction and issue the command again. 


59423  0-INFO 


59424  8-HOLD Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> bad working arm 

       Cause:
         The arm belongs to a robot family not suitable for being a worker
         arm. 

       Remedy:
         Check the correctness of parameters in the ARM_COOP predefined
         routine call. 


59425  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> bad auxiliary axes 

       Cause:
         The auxiliary axis is not part of a group of axes or is not
         suitable for being a positioner. 

       Remedy:
         Check the correctness of the configuration of the axis specified in
         the predefined routine AUX_COOP. 


59426  8-HOLD Synchronized arm cannot move 

       Cause:
         The user is trying to execute a SYNCMOVE when the synchronized arm
         cannot move (i.e. is not calibrated or is disabled or is locked). 

       Remedy:
         Check the status of the sync arm. 


59427  8-HOLD $TP_ORNT wrong value 

       Cause:
         The $TP_ORNT system variable has been assigned an invalid value. 

       Remedy:
         The value RS_TRAJ is not allowed as an orientation modality for
         jogging. Valid values are: WRIST_JNT and RPY_WORLD.

59430  12-DRIVE OFF PF T:%X Q:%X M:%X S:%X E:%X 


59431  2-WARNING Unexpected command %d %d 


59432  2-WARNING Arm <arm_num> MOVE with arm in DRIVE OFF 

       Cause:
         Motion environment has received a MOVE while the robot is in DRIVE
         OFF state. This could happen in the AUTO state with a machine in
         DRIVE ON and the other machine in DRIVE OFF and a move has been
         issued on the machine that has the drives off. 

       Remedy:
         Switch the drives on for the arm that is needed to be moved.

59435  0-INFO 


59436  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> gun axis not calibrated 

       Cause:
         It is not possible to execute MOVE statements when the gun axis is
         not calibrated. 

       Remedy:
         Calibrate the axis of the gun using the proper application program
         before executing any MOVE statement. 


59437  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> feature not available 

       Cause:
         It is not possible to enable the Soft Servo modality, because for
         this arm is not available the dynamic model compensation algorithm. 

       Remedy:
         Do not try to work in Soft Servo modality. 


59438  10-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DRIVE OFF for disabling
       the dynamic model 

       Cause:
         In order to execute the calibration or the turn-set of an axis, the
         dynamic model must be disabled for avoiding a strong variation of
         the axis position. The axis which requires the calibration /
         turn-set is brought back to the basic turn. 

       Remedy:
         It is needed to execute the calibration /turn-set upon the next
         DRIVE ON, because, being the dynamic model not enabled, the robot
         is not calibrated. 


59439  10-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> DRIVE OFF for disabling the dynamic
       model 

       Cause:
         In order to execute the calibration or the turn-set of an axis, the
         dynamic model must be disabled for avoiding  strong variations of
         the axes positions. The axes are brought back to the basic turn and
         the calibration is lost. 

       Remedy:
         It is needed to execute the calibration /turn-set upon the next
         DRIVE ON, because, being the dynamic model not enabled, the robot
         is not calibrated. 


59440  4-PAUSE Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> recovery motion not executed
       (err: <err_num>) 

       Cause:
         It is not possible to execute the recovery of the motion on the
         trajectory due to the error occurred  during the trajectory
         planning phase. 

       Remedy:
         Check the error code of the fourth parameter ant try yo remove the
         cause of it. 


59441  8-HOLD Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> axis SIK in drive off 

       Cause:
         A calibration or a turn set operation  has been issued on axes
         equipped with SIK device. The operation failed because the drives
         were off. 

       Remedy:
         Do not calibrate or turn set on axes when the state of the system
         is DRIVE OFF. Retry after having executed the AUX_DRIVES (ON)
         built-in procedure. 


59442  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> arm in turn set 

       Cause:
         It is not possible to execute MOVE statements with the arm in turn. 

       Remedy:
         Execute the turn-set procedure before issuing any MOVE. 


59443  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> thresholds not computable 

       Cause:
         It is not possible to compute the sensibility thresholds for the
         Collision Detection, because the dynamic model cannot be enabled on
         this arm. 

       Remedy:
         Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


59444  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> feature not configured 

       Cause:
         It is not possible to move the axis only with the control of the
         speed because this arm is not properly configured. 

       Remedy:
         Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


59445  10-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> bad operation with pending motion 

       Cause:
         There are pending MOVE statements already executed by the
         interpreter but not yet executed by the interpolator when the user
         is trying to calibrate/turn-set an arm. The same message is sent
         when the AUX_COOP, ARM_COOP o ARM_SOFT built-in's are executed
         during a movement; this can happen if an ADVANCE clause is present
         on a MOVE statement before the built-in's or if built-in's are just
         at the beginning of the program (at the start of the program, a
         recovery movement is performed). 

       Remedy:
         DEACTIVATE all the programs before the calibration/turn-set
         procedure. If the message is due to the cooperation, the ADVANCE
         clause before AUX_COOP, ARM_COOP o ARM_SOFT built-in's must be
         removed. If built-in's are just at the beginning of a program they
         are to be moved down or a DELAY statement is to be introduced
         before them. 


59446  8-HOLD Arm <num_arm> Robot model mismatch in requested feature 

       Cause:
         The robot model is not compatible with the requested feature. 

       Remedy:
         Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


59447  2-WARNING Arm <num_arm> Feature already enabled 

       Cause:
         The requested feature is already enabled on this arm. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message. 


59448  2-WARNING Arm <num_arm> Feature not yet enabled 

       Cause:
         The requested feature is not enabled on this arm. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message. 


59449  8-HOLD Arm <num_arm> Request in conflict with the arm status 

       Cause:
         The requested fuction ARM_MOVE RETRACT is not compatible with the
         arm status due to one of the following reasons: the robot is not on
         the interrupted trajectory (e.g. a jog movement has been executed);
         the system is in "PROG" or "LOCAL+HOLD" state; the movement has
         been aborted; the holdable program has been deactivated. 

       Remedy:
         Determine which condition occurred upon this fuction request. 


59450  2-WARNING $LIN_SPD not obtainable. Line:<line_num> 

       Cause:
         This is a warning message indicating the arm is running at a lower
         speed than $LIN_SPD specified by the user for safety reasons.

         usually occurs in most of cases during the initialization.

         (service.robotics@comau.com).

60928  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <axisType> -
       1022:Powerlink communication timeout 

       Cause:
         A problem of communication occurred on the Powerlink channel. 

       Remedy:
         Check the nodes connections. 


60929  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <axisType> - 4005:DRIVE
       ON issued with ACOPOS(IAMx) in fault 

       Cause:
         The controller cannot enter the DRIVE ON state due to the presence
         of errors in the system. 

       Remedy:
         Check additional error messages and try to reset them. 


60930  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <axisType> -
       5034:<transducerType> - homing inhibited 

       Cause:
         The encoder could be damaged, disconnected or disabled. 

       Remedy:
         Check the cabling, the encoder functionalities and the hardware
         interfaces to the ACOPOS(IAMx). 


60931  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <axisType> -
       6020:Hardware: failure in the 24VDC power supply section 

       Cause:
         Problems in the 24VDC power supply  (failure in auxiliary power
         supply, 24VDC bus connection). 

       Remedy:
         Check the assembly on the 24VDC bus, short circuits and overloads
         on the power supply section. 


60932  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <axisType> -
       6045:Hardware - anomaly in the ACOPOS(IAMx) power section 

       Cause:
         Absence of one or more motor phases, failure at the output
         ACOPOS(IAMx) stage. 

       Remedy:
         Check the phases connections on the motor, replace the ACOPOS(IAMx)
         module. 


60933  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <axisType> - 6048:axis
       braking, position error too high 

       Cause:
         The monitoring of the axis position after the braking detected a
         too high error. There is an anomaly in the motor brake. 

       Remedy:
         Check the brake status. 


60934  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <axisType> -
       6052(3,4):short circuit in motor phase 

       Cause:
         A short circuit occurred in one or more phases of the motor. 

       Remedy:
         Check the cabling and the motor functionality. 


60935  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <axisType> - 6055:brake
       short circuit 

       Cause:
         The supply voltage of the brake is insufficient. Possible causes of
         the fault: cables or connectors; 24Vdc power supply provided to the
         IAM module from the ASM module is not sufficient (voltage drop,
         power supply overload); IAM faulty (circuit brake control, level of
         verification signal); brake coil is faulty. 

       Remedy:
         Check if the connectors and wiring on the circuit 24Vdc brake are
         intact. Check the value and the stability of the supply voltage
         from the ASM32 module and replace the ASM32 module itself (24Vdc
         auxiliary power supply).  If the supply voltage of the IAM is
         correct, replace the IAM; if the problem persists, replace the
         motor. 


60936  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <axisType> - 6056:open
       brake circuit 

       Cause:
         Motor brake open circuit. 

       Remedy:
         Check the cabling of the motor and the brake functionality. 


60937  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <axisType> -
       6057:position loop control, error on encoder 

       Cause:
         Error in reading the encoder position. 

       Remedy:
         Check the cabling and the functionalities of the encoder. 


60938  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <axisType> - 6058:Enable
       1 not present in DRIVE ON state 

       Cause:
         The signal Enable1 is not present upon at a DRIVE ON state request. 

       Remedy:
         Check the correctness of the wiring on the X1 connector of
         ACOPOS(IAMx) modules. An Hardware failure could be present on
         SDM/ACOPOS(IAMx) modules. 


60939  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <axisType> - 6059:Enable
       2 not present in DRIVE ON state 

       Cause:
         The signal Enable2 is not present upon at a DRIVE ON state request. 

       Remedy:
         Check the correctness of the wiring on the X1 connector of
         ACOPOS(IAMx) modules. An Hardware failure could be present on
         SDM/ACOPOS(IAMx) modules. Check wiring from X108/SDM to X1/IAMx in
         case of main drives Also check wiring from X109/SDM to X1/IAMx in
         case of auxiliary drives Check if one of the IAM's drives is
         shorting Enable 2 signal Check 24VDC supply to SDM Check for issues
         with ASM32

       encoder - Alarm bit is set

60952  2-WARNING Board <board_num> - 7211:DC bus: Voltage drop - check the
       power line 

       Cause:
         The voltage has fallen, or dropped to a lower value. This may be
         due to a hole in the network or because one or more phases have
         failed. 

       Remedy:
         Check the value of the voltage and check the connections of the
         three phases L1, L2, L3.

       Cause:
         At least one of the three power supply phases of the drive is
         absent. 

       Remedy:
         Check the presence of the phases on the drive power supply. 


60954  10-DRIVE OFF Axis <num_asse> Arm <num_arm> - Drive not ready 

       Cause:
         L'azionamento relativo all'asse, non  sincrono (riconosciuto)
         sulla rete Powerlink, e/o,  in uno stato non idoneo a gestire la
         sua abilitazione (drive on). 

       Remedy:
         E' importante verificare la sequenza di errori precedenti, potrebbe
         non essere sufficiente una ripartenza o spegnimento del controllo,
         ma necessaria, la sostituzione del modulo. 


60955  10-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> - Homing not present 

       Cause:
         The transducer  clearing procedure (HOMING) has not been issued, or
         it did not complete due to an axis error 

       Remedy:
         Check the connections with the transducer  , eventually replace it
         if needed. Observe the sequence of errors previously occurred; if
         one of these is the cause of the lost of the calibration data (the
         axis requires a TURN-SET), it is needed a system restart or
         shutdown. 


60956  10-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> - Enabling not present 

       Cause:
         The axis enabling procedure did not complete; on the drive is
         absent the enabling signal (ENABLE). 

       Remedy:
         Check the connection on X1 of the signal coming from the SDM; if
         the problem persists, replace the drive module. 


60957  10-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> - RS RECOVERY MODE
       active 

       Cause:
         RECOVERY MODE is active (Enabling not present). ATTENTION: all safe
         functions are disabled till the completion of the procedure. 

       Remedy:
         Complete SAFE LINE UP procedure by deactivating the command on
         RoboSAFE interface or from Teach Pendant.

61439  0-INFO SYSTEM ERROR: Arm %d errore:%d sconosciuto 


61952  0-INFO 


61953  0-INFO 


61954  0-INFO 


61955  11-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> negative electrical stroke end 

       Cause:
         The axis has reached the lower negative hardware limit switch .
         This is the second protection level before the axis reaches the
         mechanical limit switch. Usually this alarm occurs when an axis
         that is not calibrated goes over the software limit or when the
         electric sensor is activated before the software checks whether the
         axis is over the limit. If this happens and the axis is calibrated,
         check the axis calibration and/or the regulation of the sensor.
         Otherwise perhaps the sensor does not receive the power supply, the
         cable may be broken or the module internal circuit that makes the
         control could be open. 

       Remedy:
         Use the alarm exclusion mode (tasto <EXCL> key ) and move the axis
         manually. 


61956  11-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> positive electrical stroke end 

       Cause:
         The axis has reached the lower negative hardware limit switch .
         This is the second protection level before the axis reaches the
         mechanical limit switch. Usually this alarm occurs when an axis
         that is not calibrated goes over the software limit or when the
         electric sensor is activated before the software checks whether the
         axis is over the limit. If this happens and the axis is calibrated,
         check the axis calibration and/or the regulation of the sensor.
         Otherwise perhaps the sensor does not receive the power supply, the
         cable may be broken or the module internal circuit that makes the
         control could be open. 

       Remedy:
         Use the alarm exclusion mode (tasto <EXCL> key ) and move the axis
         manually. 


61957  14-FATAL Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP Fault IGBT phaseU high
       arm (sts 0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         Components outside the drive broken. The current loop (DSP) has an
         error in the available hardware (<param> = stsHW). There is an
         error in the piloting state of the IGBT bridge arms. Each output
         branch of the bridge is managed separately, therefore it is
         possible to have separate error signals . The signal indicates a
         possible short circuit on the output or the earth phase or an
         internal failure of the IGBT module and/or auxiliary piloting
         circuits of the IGBT (power supplies, current sensor). 

       Remedy:
         Check the output connections from the power module , the flat cable
         connection between DSP boards and the piloting electronics . As a
         replacement possibility ,the DSP board of the faulty axis, ,the
         flat cable, the axis module can be detected . Check the motors and
         their connections . 


61958  14-FATAL Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP Fault IGBT phaseV high
       arm (sts 0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         Components outside the drive broken. The current loop (DSP) has an
         error in the available hardware (<param> = stsHW). There is an
         error in the piloting state of the IGBT bridge arms. Each output
         branch of the bridge is managed separately, therefore it is
         possible to have separate error signals . The signal indicates a
         possible short circuit on the output or the earth phase or an
         internal failure of the IGBT module and/or auxiliary piloting
         circuits of the IGBT (power supplies, current sensor).

         connection between DSP boards and the piloting electronics . As a
         replacement possibility ,the DSP board of the faulty axis, ,the
         flat cable, the axis module can be detected . Check the motors and
         their connections .

61963  14-FATAL Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP fault counting encoder
       impulses (sts 0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         The current loop (DSP) shows an hardware error (<param> = stsHW).
         The encoder reading (with Hiperface command) exceeded of 5
         mechanical degrees  the expected value calculated by the DSP
         impulse counter. Probably a breakdown or a false contact in the
         motor - encoder - connector - cable - DSP connection chain
         occurred. 

       Remedy:
         Check the encoder connection and if necessary replace the encoder
         cable. If the problem continues, replace the DSP board. 


61964  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP Temp of power module
       above maximum threshold (sts 0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         The current loop (DSP) shows a hardware error (<param> = stsHW).
         This is signalled when the temperature of the power module passes
         over the set alarm threshold. 

       Remedy:
         Check the serviceability of the rear fans and the cleanliness of
         the cabinet ventilation channel. Check the mechanical clamping of
         the axes module on the dissipater. 


61965  10-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> Temp of motor above
       maximum threshold 

       Cause:
         The motor temperature is over the maximum limit. Probably the
         connection to the motor is open. There is an interruption on one or
         more of the motor phases. The axis moves with the motor braked.
         There is usually a message that informs the user on the high
         current request from the motor. Check that the arm cycle does not
         put the motors under stress. 

       Remedy:
         Check the connections. Check that the connection to the brake is
         not open. Examine the sequence of previous alarms paying special
         attention to those with "high current request". Check the
         serviceability of the motor in the open phase. If necessary replace
         the DSP board. 


61966  0-INFO 


61967  14-FATAL Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP Resolver reading Fault.
       (sts 0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         The current loop (DSP) shows a hardware error (<param> = stsHW). It
         is quite likely that there is a breakage or a false contact in the
         motor - encoder - connector - cable - DSP chain . 

       Remedy:
         Check the resolver connection and if necessary replace the resolver
         cable. If the problem persists, replace the DSP board.

61971  14-FATAL Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP Fault Watchdog DSP. (sts

61972  14-FATAL Axis %d Arm %d DSP TRQLOOP_ERROR_1021_15. (sts 0x%x) 


61973  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP SW error: 0x<param> 

       Cause:
         The current loop (DSP) shows a software error ; this error is
         specified by the loop through a range of bits. Check the bit
         values. If bit 3 is 0, see the description of error 62010 (DSP
         Encoder not initialised); if bit 6 is 0, see the description of
         error 62009 (DSP axis not configured); if bit 13 is 0, see error
         62011 (DSP not initialised); if bit 14 is 0, see error 62012 (DSP
         external synchronism failed); if bit 15 is 0,see error 62013 (DSP
         does not acknowledge the slot identifier). 

       Remedy:
         See the remedy for the relevant error. 


61974  0-INFO 


61975  2-WARNING Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP Fault in counting
       encoder impulses (sts 0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         The current loop (DSP) shows a hardware warning (<param> = stsHW).
         This indicates a fault in the internal operation of the sinusoidal
         encoder. The alarm indication results from the acquisition of the
         encoder internal status by the relevant read command. 

       Remedy:
         The system is deteriorating in the encoder read serviceability .
         Check the motor - encoder - connector - cable - DSP chain.

       temperature above warning threshold (sts 0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         The current loop (DSP) shows a hardware warning (<param> = stsHW).
         This is shown when the power module temperature exceeds the set
         warning threshold. 

       Remedy:
         Check the serviceability of the rear fans and the cleanliness of
         the cabinet ventilation channel. Check the mechanical clamping of
         the axis module on the dissipater. 


61977  2-WARNING Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP motor temperature above
       warning thereshold (sts 0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         The current loop (DSP) shows a hardware warning (<param> = stsHW).
         This is shown when the motor temperature exceeds the set alarm
         threshold. 

       Remedy:
         Check the connections and the connection to the brake , which must
         not be open. Examine the sequence of previous alarms, especially
         those for "high current request". Check the serviceability of the
         motor in open phase. 


61978  14-FATAL Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP Fault on Hiperface
       serial line (sts 0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         The current loop (DSP) shows a hardware warning (<param> = stsHW).
         There is an error on the Hiperface serial line used to read the
         encoder. 

       Remedy:
         The system is deteriorating in the encoder read serviceability
         Check the motor - encoder - connector - cable - DSP chain. 


61979  2-WARNING Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP Fault on sinusoidal
       encoder signals (sts 0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         The current loop (DSP) shows a hardware warning (<param> = stsHW).
         There is an error on the Hiperface serial line used to read the
         encoder. 

       Remedy:
         The system is deteriorating in the encoder read serviceability.
         Check the motor- encoder - connector - cable - DSP chain. 


61980  2-WARNING Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP Warning brake command
       circuit (sts 0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         The current loop (DSP) shows a hardware warning (<param> = stsHW).
         It indicates the true state of the brake circuit and this
         information is passed through the DSP and the CPU board. If the
         system has the drives switched to on, the brake is always powered
         on, therefore the value of the bit which causes this error is
         always set to 1. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message. 


61981  2-WARNING Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP Warning incorrect drive
       full scale current value (sts 0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         The current loop (DSP) shows a hardware warning (<param> = stsHW).
         The full scale current is wrong. There is an inconsistency between
         the declared current value in the characterisation file and the
         size of the drive power module . 

       Remedy:
         Check the size of the drive power module. Replace the power module
         is the size and the declaration are correct. 


61982  2-WARNING Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> I2T triggered 

       Cause:
         The robot work cycle is stressing the axis motor and the axis is
         moving when the motor is braked. The current value the motor
         requests from the control is high. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the declarations regarding the load are correct and that
         the connection to the brake is not open. 


61983  2-WARNING Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP encoder correction
       algorithm triggered (sts 0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         The current loop (DSP) shows a hardware warning (<param> = stsHW).
         The compensation algorithm which rebuilds the encoder reading has
         run. The position value obtained counting the encoder impulses from
         the  DSP offsets more than one  mechanical degree from the position
         absolute value read by the encoder via serial line. The DSP
         attempts to recover from  the error. 

       Remedy:
         A continuous signalling indicates that the circuit linked to the
         encoder reading is being  damaged.  Check the following chain:
         motor - encoder - connector - cable - DSP. 


61984  2-WARNING Axis %d Arm %d DSP TRQLOOP_WARNING_9 (sts 0x%x) 


61985  2-WARNING Axis %d Arm %d DSP TRQLOOP_WARNING_10 (sts 0x%x) 


61986  2-WARNING Axis %d Arm %d DSP TRQLOOP_WARNING_11 (sts 0x%x) 


61987  2-WARNING Axis %d Arm %d DSP TRQLOOP_WARNING_12 (sts 0x%x) 


61988  2-WARNING Axis %d Arm %d DSP TRQLOOP_WARNING_13 (sts 0x%x) 


61989  2-WARNING Axis %d Arm %d DSP TRQLOOP_WARNING_14 (sts 0x%x) 


61990  2-WARNING Axis %d Arm %d DSP TRQLOOP_WARNING_15 (sts 0x%x) 


61991  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> following error out of
       range 

       Cause:
         The servo control is not able to keep the following error within a
         certain limit. This is because of a limited value problem of the
         currents coming from the servo drive or the state of the brake
         (braked axis). 

       Remedy:
         Analyse the maximum current value and make sure that it is
         sufficient to move the axes at maximum speed. Make sure also that
         the axes are not on the limit switch. Check that the brakes are not
         locked and that the connection to the brake is not open. Check that
         the robot is not overloaded.

61998  0-INFO 


61999  11-DRIVE OFF Arm: <servo_num> Robot Alarm 

       Cause:
         The Robot Alarm input (AllarmeRobot) is active during a DRIVE ON
         request. The drive deactivates. This means that the alarms cable
         coming from the robot is open; usually this input is used by a
         device to signal any malfunctions to the robot control. 

       Remedy:
         Check the external device connected to this alarm input or check
         the by-pass of the robot connectors or the control. 


62000  11-DRIVE OFF Arm: <servo_num> Air alarm 

       Cause:
         The input for the Air Alarm (AllarmeAria) is active during a DRIVE
         ON request; the drive deactivates. This means that the air pressure
         is not sufficient for the device 

       Remedy:
         Check the air supply and check if the robot actually needs air. 


62001  0-INFO 


62002  0-INFO 


62003  0-INFO 


62004  0-INFO 


62005  0-INFO 


62006  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> motion under no servo
       control 

       Cause:
         The servo control continues to perceive movement of a position
         transducer even if the servo loops are open. In other words, the
         transducers are moving and the servo control is not sending current
         to the motors. This could be caused by disturbance on the
         transducer reading or by the brakes that are unable to prevent
         movement of the motor. 

       Remedy:
         Check the transducer connections and inspect the axis brakes. 


62007  2-WARNING Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <type> high current
       required (<param>) 

       Cause:
         The servo control requests too much current to the motors. This may
         be because the robot cycle is too severe or because there are
         problems on the motor itself, such as a wrong phase or a closed
         brake. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the processing is executed in a satisfactory manner. If
         it is, ignore this message. Otherwise the cycle has to be changed,
         modulating the acceleration and deceleration movements where the
         error takes place, or trying to optimise the spots in the area
         involved to reduce stress on the robot. Check that the connection
         to the brake is not open. 


62008  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> mismatch in brakes
       status 

       Cause:
         The brake control status is not consistent to the signals that
         concern the brake. 

       Remedy:
         Check the brake serviceability. Connections, wiring, motor power
         supply voltage. 


62009  0-INFO 


62010  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP Encoder uninit (sts
       0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         The encoder initialising, with timer QEP and initial absolute
         position has not been executed. 

       Remedy:
         Check the encoder cable and the connection to the motor; if the
         problem persists replace the motor. 


62011  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP uninit (sts
       0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         The DSP board initialising has not taken place (the default values
         have not been set). 

       Remedy:
         Change the DSP board. 


62012  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> DSP external synchronism
       failed (sts 0x<param>) 

       Cause:
         There has been no synchronising with the external 8KHZ synchronism
         signal . 

       Remedy:
         Check the condition of the synchronism signal connection. Replace
         the DSP board. 


62013  0-INFO 


62014  0-INFO 


62015  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <type> speed out of
       limits 

       Cause:
         Servo control cannot maintain the velocity error (difference
         between the target speed and the real speed) under a certain limit.
         This can be due either to a limited value of currents coming from
         the servo drive or to the state of the brake (axis refrained). 

       Remedy:
         Verify that the maximum value of the current can move the axes at
         maximum speed. Check that the axes are not at the stroke end.
         Verify that brakes are not blocked and that the connector to the
         brake is not open. Check that the robot is not overloaded.

       (<param>) 

       Cause:
         The parameter indicates an error directly returned from the drive
         module. 

       Remedy:
         Please contact Comau (service.robotics@comau.com) providing the
         error code reported as parameter in the message. 


62019  11-DRIVE OFF PPS <board_num> error <error> 

       Cause:
         The parameter indicates an error directly returned from the PPS
         module. 

       Remedy:
         Please contact Comau (service.robotics@comau.com) providing the
         error code reported as parameter in the message.

       Cause:

       Remedy:

         error code reported as parameter in the message.
