62023  10-DRIVE OFF Asse <num_asse> Arm <num_arm> (SFM) additional motor
       fan not active 

       Cause:
         In DRIVE ON state, the additional fan, dedicated to the cooling of
         the motor, is not active or is not working. 

       Remedy:
         Please check the connections, the cables, the supply voltage
         related to the SupplyFanMotor (SFM) option. 


62024  10-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> persistent high current 

       Cause:
         The current required for the axis persists for more than 500
         milliseconds. 

       Remedy:
         The cycle time is not acceptable or the axis characterization is
         not correct; please check the size-motor-drive association. 


62025  10-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <type> CRCOPEN
       discontinuous positional target 

       Cause:
         The test on targets addressed to the C5G controller failed. The
         PC/CRCOPEN controller  required too far away positions. 

       Remedy:
         Please check the targets generator on the PC/CRCOPEN controller. 


62026  10-DRIVE OFF  Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <type> CRCOPEN
       discontinuous speed target 

       Cause:
         The test on targets addressed to the C5G controller failed. The
         PC/CRCOPEN controller  required too far away speeds. 

       Remedy:
         Please check the target generator on the PC/CRCOPEN controller. 


62027  10-DRIVE OFF  Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <type> CRCOPEN
       discontinuous current target 

       Cause:
         The test on targets addressed to the C5G controller failed. The
         PC/CRCOPEN controller  required too far away currents. 

       Remedy:
         Please check the target generator on the PC/CRCOPEN controller. 


62028  11-DRIVE OFF PowerLink AMS-PPS (<board>) module in OFF 

       Cause:
         The PowerLink AMS-PassivePowerSupply (Module ID="SL1.IF2.ST<
         board>") module entered the OFF state (yellow led is switched off).
         The system will automatically try to switch the module ON upon next
         DRIVE ON. 

       Remedy:
         Please check that the module is properly positioned and screwed; if
         the problem persists, please replace the module. 


62029  10-DRIVE OFF Asse <num_asse> Arm <num_arm> (SLS) Slide
       Lubrification Supply not active 

       Cause:
         In DRIVE ON state, the Slide Lubrification Supply, is not active or
         is not working. 

       Remedy:
         Please check the connections, the cables, the supply voltage
         related to the C5G-SLS SLIDE LUBRIFICATION SUPPLY (SLS) option.

62464  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> target position out of range 

       Cause:
         Firmware error. 

       Remedy:
         Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


62465  2-WARNING Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> positive stroke end 

       Cause:
         The arm is near the positive limit of the available range for this
         axis. It is not possible to move the arm further. 

       Remedy:
         Reenter the available workspace of the robot. 


62466  2-WARNING Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> negative stroke end 

       Cause:
         The arm is near the negative limit of the available range for this
         axis. Is not possible to move the arm further. 

       Remedy:
         Reenter the available workspace of the robot. 


62467  0-INFO 


62468  0-INFO 


62469  10-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> tolerance unobtainable 

       Cause:
         The arm is not able to enter the joint tolerance with those
         programmable parameters. 

       Remedy:
         Change the setting of $TERM_TYPE from FINE to COARSE if it is
         possible for the application, or increase the tolerance range
         ($TOL_JNT[][axis]) and switch the controller off and on. If the
         cycle is now executed correctly, save the new predefined variable
         in .C5G, or increase the time ($TOL_TOUT) but this increases the
         cycle time. 


62470  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> position out of tolerance 

       Cause:
         The arm is not able to enter into a sphere with those programmable
         parameters. 

       Remedy:
         The radius of the sphere is too small. It is possible to increase
         it changing $TOL_FINE. If it is possible for the particular
         application, the problem could be solved by changing the setting of
         $TERM_TYPE from FINE to COARSE or it is possible to increase the
         time ($TOL_TOUT) but this increases the cycle time. 


62471  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> HOLD due to singularity 

       Cause:
         If the predefined variable $SING_CARE is set TRUE or Sensor
         Tracking is enabled, the controller indicates to the user that the
         position of the robot is near to a singularity. 

       Remedy:
         If the predefined variable is set FALSE, the controller tries to
         reach the singularities by limiting the joints speed; this is
         possible only for some kind of robots. If Sensor Tracking is
         enabled it is not possible to avoid this situation and the user
         should move the robot out of the singularity. 


62472  8-HOLD Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> HOLD Cartesian limit + 

       Cause:
         The arm is near the positive limit of the available range for an
         axis. It is not possible to move the arm further or the arm cannot
         reach the position due to its kinematics. 

       Remedy:
         Change the final position. 


62473  8-HOLD Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> HOLD Cartesian limit - 

       Cause:
         The arm is near the negative limit of the available range for an
         axis. It is not possible to move the arm further or the arm cannot
         reach the position due to its kinematics. 

       Remedy:
         Change the final position. 


62474  0-INFO 


62475  11-DRIVE OFF CPU <num_cpu> safety chain open as error 

       Cause:
         A fatal error caused the opening of the safety chain. 

       Remedy:
         Remove or analyze and solve the previous error first. 


62476  0-INFO 


62477  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> Cartesian position out of range 

       Cause:
         The Cartesian position is out of the available workspace for this
         arm. 

       Remedy:
         Change the position. 


62478  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> axis 1 at undefined position 

       Cause:
         The arm, typically a SMART robot, has the center of the wrist
         aligned with the z-axis of the world frame. This is an arm
         singularity. 

       Remedy:
         Avoid entering the center of the wrist in a cylindrical volume
         coaxial to the z-axis. 


62479  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> wrist axis at undefined position 

       Cause:
         The wrist, typically a SMART wrist, has axis 5 at zero position.
         For this wrist, it is impossible to independently compute the
         values of axes 4, 5, and 6. 

       Remedy:
         Avoid working in Cartesian space with axis 5 at zero position or,
         if implemented, change the setting of $ORNT_TYPE to WRIST_JNT in
         order to execute the trajectory in Cartesian, but interpolate the
         wrist axes in joint. 


62480  2-WARNING Arm <arm_num> axis 2/3 at open stroke end 

       Cause:
         The arm is a robot with the same kinematics for axes 2 and 3. Due
         to the parallelogram it is not possible to move axis 2 and axis 3
         independently. For the reciprocal joint position they are at the
         maximum open configuration. 

       Remedy:
         Reenter the available workspace of the robot. 


62481  2-WARNING Arm <arm_num> axis 2/3 at closed stroke end 

       Cause:
         The arm is a robot with the same kinematics for axes 2 and 3. Due
         to the parallelogram it is not possible to move axis 2 and axis 3
         independently. For the reciprocal joint position they are at the
         maximum close configuration. 

       Remedy:
         Reenter the available workspace of the robot. 


62482  10-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> tolerance HOLD
       unobtainable 

       Cause:
         It is not possible to obtain the tolerance after a HOLD. 

       Remedy:
         Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


62483  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> axis 5 at undefined position 

       Cause:
         The wrist has axis 5 at an undefined position. 

       Remedy:
         Avoid working in Cartesian space with axis 5 at this undefined
         position or, if implemented, change the setting of $ORNT_TYPE to
         WRIST_JNT in order to execute the trajectory in Cartesian, but
         interpolate the wrist axes in joint. 


62484  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> inverse kinematics not available 

       Cause:
         This machine does not have the inverse kinematics. Or, in case of
         compensation algorithm active, it means that the programmed Joint
         or Cartesian position cannot be compensated. 

       Remedy:
         Do not try to work in Cartesian. Or, in case of compensation
         algorithm active, program the Joint or Cartesian position out of
         the area where the compensation cannot work. 


62485  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> bad interpolator target
       position 

       Cause:
         A check of the targets in the servo control environment failed. The
         interpolator is requesting target positions too far ahead. 

       Remedy:
         Change the position if possible.  Please contact  COMAU
         (service.robotics@comau.com). 


62486  12-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> ADVANCE or new jog motion not allowed 

       Cause:
         The machine has changed configuration due to a singularity. Neither
         the ADVANCE clause nor a new jog motion are allowed. 

       Remedy:
         Either avoid moving through singularity points, do not use the
         ADVANCE clause, or release all jog buttons before pressing a new
         one. 


62487  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> Seam Track parameters out of range 

       Cause:
         Some initialization parameters of the Seam Track have been set at a
         wrong value. 

       Remedy:
         Compare the value with the corresponding range. 


62488  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> Seam Track synchronisms not in sequence 

       Cause:
         Seam Track detected an error in weaving synchronism from system.
         This can happen with Cartesian weaving along very short movement
         joined in fly if $FLY_TYPE is set to FLY_NORM. 

       Remedy:
         $FLY_TYPE must be set at FLY_CART value. 


62489  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> Seam Track synchronism overrun 

       Cause:
         During arc sensor tracking with weaving there is an overlap of
         reading phases from the analogic input. This happens if weaving
         frequency is too high or if the time delay between the theoretical
         and real targets is too long. 

       Remedy:
         Check Seam Track parameters for time delay or reduce the weaving
         frequency. 


62490  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> Seam Track synchronism timeout 

       Cause:
         The weaving synchronism from the system to Seam Track do not arrive
         on time. This happens only if a time-out is programmed on Seam
         Track (usually time-out check is disabled). 

       Remedy:
         Increase the time-out or remove this feature by setting the Seam
         Track time-out to zero. 


62491  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> Seam Track corrections out of range 

       Cause:
         Seam Track has detected corrections out of the threshold for a long
         period. Usually this is due to an instability of the welding
         current or to a wrong value of the threshold. 

       Remedy:
         Check the threshold on the maximum corrections; verify the welding
         parameters and the workpiece surface conditions. 


62492  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> Seam Track board error 

       Cause:
         Seam Track has detected an internal error. 

       Remedy:
         Board could be damaged. 


62493  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> total corrections out of range 

       Cause:
         The distance between the robot and the programmed trajectory has
         exceeded the threshold defined in $SENSOR_OFST_LIM. This is a
         safety guard to stop the robot in the case of sensor failure. 

       Remedy:
         Check the sensor or increase $SENSOR_OFST_LIM. 


62494  11-DRIVE OFF CPU <num_cpu> interpolation overrun 

       Cause:
         The interpolator sampling time is too short. 

       Remedy:
         The interpolator sampling time has to be increased. Please, contact
         COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


62495  2-WARNING Arm <arm_num> axis 1 at open stroke end 

       Cause:
         The arm is near the open stroke end for axis 1. Is not possible to
         move the arm further. 

       Remedy:
         Reenter the available workspace of the robot. 


62496  2-WARNING Arm <arm_num> axis 1 at closed stroke end 

       Cause:
         The arm is near the close stroke end for axis 1. Is not possible to
         move the arm further. 

       Remedy:
         Reenter the available workspace of the robot.

       Cause:

       Remedy:

62504  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> out of the conveyor window 

       Cause:
         This error occurs when the robot moves out of the conveyor window. 

       Remedy:
         Change the program so that all the movements stay within the window
         limits. 


62505  2-WARNING Arm <arm_num> pos out of work zone 

       Cause:
         The position or joint position is not in the correct zone of work. 

       Remedy:
         Change the position or joint position. 


62506  0-INFO 


62507  0-INFO 


62508  4-PAUSE Arm <arm_num> jog keys combination not allowed 

       Cause:
         The machine configuration does not allow these jog keys: this is
         true, for example, in case of a robot with missing axes, in case of
         electrical welding gun when a Cartesian frame of reference is used
         , in case of axes under speed control. This also happens  in case
         of cooperative motion active or in presence of remote tool or
         conveyor. 

       Remedy:
         Only use the allowed jog keys for this  machine configuration. 


62509  0-INFO 


62510  0-INFO 


62511  11-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> forbidded motion for integrated arm 

       Cause:
         The first arm of a couple of integrated arms (the carrier) moved in
         a non syncronized way while the second arm was executing a
         linear/circular movement on a JOINTPOS or a JOINT movement on a
         POSITION/XTNDPOS. 

       Remedy:
         Move the two arms with a SYNCMOVE statement or try to maintain
         steady the first arm while executing this particular type of motion
         with the second. Note that the first arm is allowed to move while
         the second arm is doing LINEAR/CIRCULAR movements on a
         POSITION/XTNDPOS or JOINT movements on a JOINTPOS. 


62512  4-PAUSE Arm <arm_num> Cartesian Position not compensable 

       Cause:
         In case of compensation algorithm active, it means that the
         programmed Joint  or Cartesian position cannot be compensated. 

       Remedy:
         In case of compensation algorithm active, program the Joint  or 
         Cartesian position out of the area where the compensation cannot
         work. 


62513  10-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> collision detected 

       Cause:
         An anomalous request  of corrent has been requested and this can be
         due to an arm collision. 

       Remedy:
         Check if a collision occurred and if damage has been caused. Then
         modify the program that performs motion. In case no crash occurred,
         check if the payload declared is correct. If yes, check the value
         assigned to the sensitivity threshold that are used for detecting
         potential collisions. 


62514  2-WARNING Arm <arm_num> Collision detection disabled in DRIVE OFF 

       Cause:
         Due to drive off state, the collision detection has been disabled. 

       Remedy:
         Retry enabling the collision detection upon DRIVE ON. 


62515  0-INFO 


62516  0-INFO 


62517  13-FATAL CPU <num_cpu> wrong numerical representation 

       Cause:
         The mathematical calculation detected a wrong numerical
         representation during the determination of target quotes 

       Remedy:
         Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


62518  11-DRIVE OFF CPU <num_cpu> Time-out Softservo for collision 

       Cause:
         The maximum time foreseen for the softservo state due to collision
         expired. 

       Remedy:
         Check if a collision occurred and if damage has been caused. 


62519  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> Weave shape not obtainable 

       Cause:
         The length of weave is too short for being executed. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the length of weave is greater than the sum of the
         waiting segments and of the space needed fot reaching the amplitude
         required. 


62520  2-WARNING Arm <arm_num> determination of collision thresholds
       completed 

       Cause:
         The process for the determination of Collision Detection thresholds
         has completed. 

       Remedy:
         This is just an informational message. 


62521  13-FATAL Arm <arm_num> anomaly in dynamic model determination 

       Cause:
         Mathematics computations determined a wrong numeric representation
         of the current of the dynamic model. 

       Remedy:
         Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


62522  8-HOLD Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> joint trasversal speed not
       obtainable 

       Cause:
         The requested trasversal speed cannot be obtained. 

       Remedy:
         Please check, from the characterization, the maximum speed which
         can be obtained by the axis. 


62523  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> trasversal speed not obtainable 

       Cause:
         The requested Cartesian trasversal speed cannot be obtained. 

       Remedy:
         Please check, from the characterization,the maximum speed which can
         be obtained in linear movements. 


62524  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> insuff.space for reaching the trasversal speed 

       Cause:
         The programmed space for Cartesian weaving cannot reach the
         programmed speed. 

       Remedy:
         Increase the space or change the trasversal speed. 


62525  8-HOLD Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> insuff.space for trasversal
       speed 

       Cause:
         The programmed space for joint weaving is not sufficient for
         reaching the programmed speed. 

       Remedy:
         Increase the space or the trasversal speed. 


62526  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> semi-period weaving speeds are in conflict 

       Cause:
         In the planning of the weaving table, both speeds in the same
         semi-period have to be different than zero. 

       Remedy:
         Please check that the round trip speeds on the left and right
         semi-waves are different than zero. 


62527  4-PAUSE Arm <arm_num> jog keys on disabled axes 

       Cause:
         Jog keys being used are related to disabled axes, like, for
         example, the axes equipped with a safety device or axes which are
         in a state protected by the system (for example not calibrated axes
         and a mutual stroke end). 

       Remedy:
         Please use jog keys associated to enabled axes only or check the
         eventuality of other kind of limitations. 


62528  2-WARNING Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> overloaded reducer 

       Cause:
         The working cycle detected an overloading of the reducer. The life
         of the reducer is of sure effected by the way of use. 

       Remedy:
         Modify the motion program or the payload applied to the robot. 


62529  8-HOLD Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> position stroke end 

       Cause:
         During a JOG session of an influencing arm, the motor of the
         influenced arm has reached the extremes of the working area of the
         base turn. Usually the axis is controlled with the speed loop. 

       Remedy:
         Move the axis in JOG after having selected the arm which owns it. 


62530  4-PAUSE Arm <arm_num> reference not null 

       Cause:
         The $BASE frame has been declared not null on the arm of the
         SMARTLASER optical bench. 

       Remedy:
         Do not change the $BASE frame otherwise a correct movement of the
         integrated arms is not guaranteed. 


62531  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> not enough space on the disk for MultiPass 

       Cause:
         There is not enough space on the disk for storing the data
         necessary for executing Sensor Tracking with Multipass. 

       Remedy:
         Delete all files which are not used for Sensor Tracking in: "TD:\"
         and "UD:\data\multipass". 


62532  2-WARNING Arm <arm_num> sensor disabled during the TEACH MultiPass
       phase 

       Cause:
         The predefined ARM_MULTIPASS  routine has been called for the TEACH
         phase while the Sensor tracking was disabled ($SENSOR_ENBL:=FALSE). 

       Remedy:
         Enable the Sensor Tracking ($SENSOR_ENBL:=TRUE) before calling the
         predefined ARM_MULTIPASS routine or before clearing the offset
         value for the Sensor Track during the TEACH multipass phase. 


62533  8-HOLD Arm <arm_num> Ecam disabled due to error 

       Cause:
         The automatic recovery of the cam cannot be executed due to an
         error. 

       Remedy:
         Manually move the arm to a $HOME position. 


62534  0-INFO 


62535  10-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> movement not allowed with axes pursuit
       option activated 

       Cause:
         It wasn't possible to move the axes of the SLAVE arm, as the Axes
         Pursuit option is active on the system. The problem could be caused
         since a program for the movement of SLAVE arm is active on the
         system, whilst the Axes Pursuit feature is active on it. 

       Remedy:
         If it is necessary to move the SLAVE axes in automatic mode, please
         be sure that the $AX_PURSUIT_ENBL variable has been set to FALSE.
         On the contrary if it is necessary to move the system in automatic
         mode with the Axes Pursuit feature active, it is necessary that
         there are no programmed movements on the SLAVE arm: deactivate all
         the programs for the movement of the SLAVE arm. 


62536  2-WARNING Arm <arm_num> movement not allowed with MGD while in T2
       mode 

       Cause:
         It is not allowed to move the robot with MGD when the selector is
         in T2 mode. 

       Remedy:
         Check the state of the selector and verify that the system is not
         in T2 mode. Remind that it is possible to use MGD only in
         programming mode T1. 


62537  8-HOLD Error in bend parameters in $TRK_TBL[<numtbl>] 

       Cause:
         There are errors in the description of the geometric bend
         parameters. 

       Remedy:
         Check inserted parameters for the geometric characterization of the
         bend. 


62538  2-WARNING Arm <arm_num> wrist axes at reciprocal positive stroke
       end 

       Cause:
         The reciprocal joint positions reached the maximum positive
         configuration. 

       Remedy:
         Reenter the available workspace of the robot. 


62539  2-WARNING Arm <arm_num> wrist axes at reciprocal negative stroke
       end 

       Cause:
         The reciprocal joint positions reached the maximum negative
         configuration. 

       Remedy:
         Reenter the available workspace of the robot. 


62540  11-DRIVE OFF Port in $TRK_TBL[<arm_num>] not connected 

       Cause:
         The requested port required in the table for the track application
         is not connected. 

       Remedy:
         Check the connection of the port related to the tracking. 


62541  2-WARNING IR <axis_num> reached by Arm <arm_num> 

       Cause:
         Robot reached the boundings of the forbidden Interference Region. 

       Remedy:
         Take the robot away from the forbidden Interference Region. 


62542  2-WARNING IR <param_1> reached by Axis <param_2> Arm <param_3> 

       Cause:
         Robot reached the boundings of the forbidden joint Interference
         Region. 

       Remedy:
         Take the robot away from the forbidden Interference Region. 


62543  8-HOLD Arm <num_arm> weaving modality not compatible 

       Cause:
         The requested weaving modality is not compatible with weaving
         without robot motion. 

       Remedy:
         Change the weaving modality. 


62544  10-DRIVE OFF Arm <num_arm> axes 4 and/or 6 not calibrated: please
       jog carefully (Latch) 

       Cause:
         Due to the fact that the stroke-ends of axes 4 and/or 6 are
         mutually dependent, the jog operation must be executed with
         caution. It will not be possible to jog axis 6 until axis 4 will be
         calibrated or brought to a position next to zero. 

       Remedy:
         Please unlatch the error and proceed with the jogging phase. 


62545  4-PAUSE Arm <num_arm> axis 4 to be calibrated or to be moved to
       calibration position 

       Cause:
         Axis 6 cannot be jogged when axis 4 is either not calibrated or is
         not in the calibration position. 

       Remedy:
         Execute axis 4 calibration or move it to the calibration position. 


62546  2-WARNING Arm <num_arm> weaving cannot be executed in PROG 

       Cause:
         It is not possible to execute the required weaving respecting the
         safety speed in PROG. 

       Remedy:
         Weaving with the required characteristics and speed can only be
         executed in AUTO-L or AUTO-R state. 


62547  10-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> safety speed beyond the limit 

       Cause:
         $SAFE_SPD variable has been set to a value which exceeds the safety
         foreseen limit. 

       Remedy:
         Assign a value within the safety limits. 


62548  10-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> wrong checksum on the safety speed 

       Cause:
         The checksum executed on all parameters considered by the algorithm
         related to the safety speed is not consistent. 

       Remedy:
         Perform a restart. If the problem persists, it means that it is
         related to the memory, replace then the APC. 


62549  10-DRIVE OFF Arm <arm_num> values for safety speed modified 

       Cause:
         At least one value of a predefined variable related to the
         algorithm of safety speed has been changed. 

       Remedy:
         Perform a ConfigureSave and a Restart. 


62550  10-DRIVE OFF Asse <num_asse> Arm <num_arm> tolerance SAFE C2-C3
       unobtainable 


62551  13-FATAL Arm <num_arm> anomaly in Variable Saturation determination 

       Cause:
         Mathematics computations determined a wrong numeric representation
         of Variable Saturation. 

       Remedy:
         Please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com). 


62552  10-DRIVE OFF Arm <num_arm> SAFE LINE UP mismatch, needed Reload RS 

       Cause:
         Represents a user-defined calibration position saved upon the
         download of the project and data to the safe logic. It will be used
         later on to check if the $CAL_USER is still consistent with the
         equivalent joint position saved in the safe logic. 

       Remedy:
         Execute the Reload SafeLogic.

64035  11-DRIVE OFF ACOPOS: error EPL_ACP_InitConfiguration <<error>> 


64036  11-DRIVE OFF ACOPOS: error EPL_ACP_InitDeviceNodes <%d> 


64037  11-DRIVE OFF ACOPOS: error <<error>> during the startup of the
       Ethernet Powerlink nodes 

       Cause:
         Malfunction of robot CPU (the orange APC820 module); malfunction of
         robot power supply (the grey P0220 module); corruption of CPU
         firmware; malfunction/bad connection of Powerlink cable between CPU
         and power supply. <error> 10530 : The startup function was
         interrupted 

       Remedy:
         Please examine the previous errors in order to identify the address
         (if reported) of the module which is not recongnized on the
         Powerlink network. Please check the connection and eventually
         replace the ACOPOS module. If it is loacated at address 16, the
         anomaly could be the PPS or the APC820; in such a case, please
         replace them starting with the PPS and then with the APC820.

64049  10-DRIVE OFF ACOPOS: controller restart is needed (PPS error) 

       Cause:
         If the error occurs during a system upgade, as a consequence of the
         firmware download on drives modules, it is needed to perform a
         system restart. 

       Remedy:
         Check how PPS module is installed (proper alignment of module on
         bus, tightening torque of Allen screws as described in control unit
         maintenance manual); check if contacts on high voltage bus and
         auxiliary one bus are in proper position without effort. Restart
         control unit. 


64050  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <slv_ax> motor size is
       not compatible with the data file 

       Cause:
         The size of the motor is not compatible with what declared in the
         data file. 

       Remedy:
         Please check the declaration of the motor size. 


64051  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <slv_ax> Incorrect drive
       full scale current value 

       Cause:
         The full scale current is wrong. There is an inconsistency between
         the declared current value in the characterisation file and the
         size of the drive power module . 

       Remedy:
         Check the size of the drive power module. Replace the power module
         is the size and the declaration are correct.

       the motor cannot be handled <param1> <param2> <param3> 

       Cause:

       Remedy:

         motor.

64054  11-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <slv_ax> New
       drive-motor-transducer element 

       Cause:
         Upon system restart, a difference has been detected (in respect to
         the situation before the system switching off) in the
         "drives-motor-transduction" chain. This can be due to an
         intentional  action, like the substitution of an element, or to a
         wrong coupling of controller-motor. 

       Remedy:
         Find the element which differs comparing the
         "Mtr_Arm<narm>_Ax<nax>_info.xml (.bkm)" file in "UD:\SYS\CNFG" with
         the information shown in the TP Sys_info pages. 


64055  10-DRIVE OFF Axis <axis_num> Arm <arm_num> <slv_ax> Clearing of TRC
       is requested 

       Cause:
         An element of the drive-motor-transducer chain has been replaced. 

       Remedy:
         Please clear the TRC compensation using the proper command of the
         TRC tool.

64567  0-INFO No latch space available 

       Cause:
         An attempt was made to register a latched alarm but there is no
         more space 

       Remedy:
         Verify the number of latched alarms already active 


64568  0-INFO No such latched alarm 

       Cause:
         The specified latched alarm does not exist 

       Remedy:
         Verify the error number provided 


64569  2-WARNING New system software detected
       <ver_sw_major>.<ver_sw_minor>.<ver_sw_build> 

       Cause:
         New software has been detected. 

       Remedy:
         Remove the latched alarm. 


64570  4-PAUSE Invalid IP address 

       Cause:
         Invalid IP address specified 

       Remedy:
         Check the address specified is in IP format ie. abc.def.ghi.jkl 


64571  0-INFO Permission denied 

       Cause:
         The file's permission setting does not allow the specified access.
         This error signifies that an attempt was made to access a file (or,
         in some cases, a directory) in a way that is incompatible with the
         file's attributes. 

       Remedy:
         Change the type of access requested or change the protection
         settings on the file. 


64572  0-INFO DNS / Router failed. Error: <error_num> 

       Cause:
         The initialisation of DNS/Router has failed due to the specified
         reason 

       Remedy:
         Check the reported error 


64573  4-PAUSE Failed to add host 

       Cause:
         Unable to add a host name. 

       Remedy:
         This is a startup problem so please check the board data
         configuration and the bootlines. 


64574  4-PAUSE Host/gateway init failure. Error: %d 

       Cause:
         The operation to read the hosts or gateway file failed with the
         specified error. 

       Remedy:
         Review the specified error as to why it failed. 


64575  0-INFO CD-ROM not mounted 

       Cause:
         An attempt to perform an operation on a CD which is not yet
         mounted, loaded. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the CD is loaded. 


64576  0-INFO No floppy disk/media present 

       Cause:
         An attempt was made to perform an operation on a floppy disk or an
         external device which is not yet mounted, loaded. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the floppy or the media is loaded,present and
         recognised. 


64577  0-INFO Unknown CDROM format 

       Cause:
         A CDROM has been masterized with a format not ISO9660 compatible. 

       Remedy:
         Check the state of the CDROM and that the format is ISO9660. 


64578  0-INFO Write protected disk 

       Cause:
         Attempt of writing on a device that is write protected. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the write protect device is not active. Please note
         that, as well as for floppy disks, also the DiskOnKey on USB can be
         write protected. 


64579  0-INFO Disk not formatted 

       Cause:
         Attempt of accessing to an unformatted device. 

       Remedy:
         Format the disk and try again. 


64580  0-INFO Application module not valid 

       Cause:
         Attempt of opening an application module that is noy compatible
         with the operating system version running on the CPU. 

       Remedy:
         Update the CPU software. 


64581  0-INFO Error in reading the module file 

       Cause:
         The device or the file containing the application module is
         damaged. 

       Remedy:
         Update the CPU software. 


64582  0-INFO Bad CRC module 

       Cause:
         The file containing the application module is damaged. 

       Remedy:
         Update the CPU software. 


64583  0-INFO The file is not a COMAU system file 

       Cause:
         The file specified is not a COMAU system file. 

       Remedy:
         Verify the name of the file specified.

       <ver_sw_major>.<ver_sw_minor>.<ver_sw_build> 

       Cause:
         The system has been started with a new bootup sequence. This is a
         latched alarm. 

       Remedy:
         Remove the alarm from the latched state.

         properly set in the system parameters. 


64591  0-INFO Invalid address of SNTP server 

       Cause:
         The SNTP address is not valid. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the specified SNTP server exists in the network. 


64592  0-INFO Invalid requested timeout 

       Cause:
         The timeout for the SNTP request is invalid. 

       Remedy:
         Check that the timeout is greater than zero or equal to -1.

       Cause:

       Remedy:

       Remedy:

       Remedy:

       Cause:

       Remedy:

64597  0-INFO Element already exist 

       Cause:
         The specified element already exist. 

       Remedy:

64598  0-INFO IP address/netmask clashes with another one in the system 

       Cause:
         The specified subnet (IP address/netmask) is incompatible with
         either the Teach Pendant or Shared Memory Network subnet. 

       Remedy:
         Verify the subnets of the Teach Pendant and of the Shared Memory
         Network and choose a different address/netmask. 


64599  0-INFO Board main interface subnetmask not valid 

       Cause:
         The board subnet mask is not valid. 

       Remedy:
         Verify the bootline settings. They must be on the form:
         IPAddress:SubnetMask. E.g. AAA.BBB.CCC.DDD:FFFF0000. 


64600  0-INFO Shared Memory IP address clashes with board subnet 

       Cause:
         The Shared Memory Network IP address/netmask is incompatible with
         the board public subnet. 

       Remedy:
         Verify the board subnet and choose a different address/netmask for
         the Shared Memory Network. 


64601  0-INFO Teach Pendant IP address clashes with board subnet 

       Cause:
         The Teach Pendant IP address/netmask is incompatible with the board
         public subnet. 

       Remedy:
         Verify the board subnet and choose a different address/netmask for
         the Teach Pendant.

       Cause:
         The Teach Pendant IP address/netmask is incompatible with the
         Shared Memory Network subnet. 

       Remedy:

         address/netmask for the Teach Pendant.

64625  0-INFO Access Point restart in progress 

       Cause:
         A configuration parameter of the Access Point is different from
         what expected. 

       Remedy:
         The system automatically re-programs the Access Point and restarts
         it for activating the new configuration. Please check that this
         procedure is not executed at each restart and/or switches the robot
         controller off.

       Cause:

         different than the default. 

       Remedy:

         that this procedure is not executed at each restart and/or switches
         the robot controller off.

       Cause:

         transmission parameter in the configuration of Access Point. The
         setting is incompatible with the assigned profile. 

       Remedy:

         static way the parameter to the <value> indicated in the selected
         message.

       Cause:

         procedure. The WiTP has uncoupled, but with error. 

       Remedy:
         If it is needed to uncouple the WiTP, repeat the pairing procedure
         and, in case of repeated anomalies and/or failures, report this
         error to COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com).

         completed.

         zero, meaning that the operation has been successfull. Otherwise, 
         report the error parameter to COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com).

       Remedy:

         please contact COMAU (service.robotics@comau.com) providing the
         error code and parameters.
